title: The app fits what I am looking for!
body: I‚Äôm lovin‚Äô this app so far, just into it for a week.  I was tracking most of my diet info in a spreadsheet prior  and I really like the ease and availability of the food selections and their specs along with their crisp, easy to read presentation, nice Job! I switch between the web app while at my computer and I really like the graphs to see where I‚Äôm at. Just started to look through what‚Äôs offered in premium and I would definitely pay for these features as I finely tune my usage and become proficient with it, but honestly I think your sweet spot right now is between $2.99 and $3.99 per month.  Bigger and more graphs on the mobile and web app would be great!  Until people like myself get enough time to use and appreciate the app and assess its value, your higher price is a psychological hurdle, at least for me.  I‚Äôve learned to trust my gut in app purchases and the fact that I did not jump in immediately confirms that.  I‚Äôll certainly have more feedback as I get into it further. Overall, I think you guys are on the right track with a really nice app and I‚Äôm anxious to see what‚Äôs coming next!

title: Great app & preferred over myfitness pal
body: I enjoy the layout & design of the app. I love that it doesn‚Äôt bother me too much or shame me when I don‚Äôt track calories or log a workout(?) That was an issue I found with myfitnesspal. The online forums also seem a bit more active and encouraging on this app. The app design is simple & to the point. Nutritional facts are seemingly on point. Not a hard app to figure out at all & they have a broad range of food options and choices. I‚Äôve only found it hard to find nutritional info for obscure Asian snacks. In that case, I try to track for something comparable and factor in calories from the packaging to match my food diary. I love the weigh-in function and the data charts available. You are also not inundated by ads and not at risk of accidentally pressing on an ad and opening a new webpage so that‚Äôs a big win for me! Great app, I would highly recommend to anyone who just wants to keep an easy and accurate food diary. Whatever your fitness or weight loss goals, this is a great app in general to aid those goals.

title: Love it
body: I love using fatsecret. The diary and logs and support from other users is excellent and so helpful in my weightless journey. Love the fact that you can set your own macros and calories or have it calculated for you. Tracking is mostly easy and the library of foods is extensive. That being said I noticed sometimes, not all the time, they are a little off. For example my protein I use has 3 grams sugar and when I scan the barcode the app says 0 sugar. So for people who are needing to be exact on their counts you need to just double check that they have it correctly in the system. Also, when you get notifications that someone has responded to your diary log you have to go through some steps to get to the exact message. I wish the notification center would take you directly to the message for easy reply or viewing. Only other complaint is that you have to use the online version to change your profile picture and get access to certain features but that isn't a deal breaker for me. The app does everything you need it to.  Other than that I love this app and will continue using it.

title: Comprehensive weight loss app that's easy to use!
body: This is the best weight loss app ever. I have used a few others but they do not compare. You can customize what you want to track, whether carbs, protein, fat etc. It also gives you the full nutritional breakdown of your meals, including salt and cholesterol percentages which is awesome. The recipes are fantastic and you can even participate in community conversations with fellow app users for those that want support. Adding food/recognizing label codes are super easy to do. My 5 stars are more like 4.5 stars. I took off half a star because a few times the barcode reader can be a bit off when scanning items. exp...The label may say 10 carbs or calories etc, but what is registered may be a higher or lower number. So at the end of the day your total count may be off by a few digits. Not sure if it is the fault of the app or the barcode. Either way, it is a mild nuisance that doesn't occur often enough to be problematic. With that being said, the app is awesome and I 100% recommend it.

title: Better than expected
body: Having type 2 diabetes, I used to use the ‚ÄúDiabetes In Check‚Äù app, which included specific features for diabetics. Even then, when entering some new food item I always went to the Fat Secret web site to look up nutrition information.

title: App Inaccuracies
body: The app has things like general common vegetables: kale, tomatoes, zucchini, etc where your calorie and carb count is definitely a lot different than that of other apps. This makes it difficult to track the carbs and protein in our meal. It would be great for general items like that if you added the ability to change the size of the general tomato by ounce and adjust calories proportionally.. Instead, we are tied to a medium tomato with XYZ calories... It would be best to take the general calorie averages of all brands of tomatoes and then add them in that way..

title: Good, but...
body: I have been using the app for two weeks now, primarily the diet diary function. I appreciate the wide variety of options when I search for a particular food. However, the app freezes while I'm searching and adding foods during almost every meal entry. Any items that I have "saved" are lost. I have to fully close the app, re-open, and re-enter lost items for that meal. It's frustrating. Also, I took off a star of the horrible, tacky name "FatSecret". What kind of name is that? Is the app calling users fat? Is the app a secret cure to fatness? It sounds unprofessional.

title: Fatphobic as it gets!
body: When starting out with this app, it‚Äôll prompt you your goals (weight gain or loss & how much you‚Äôd like to gain or lose) & physical attributes (height, current weight, activity levels, etc.). Being extremely underweight like I am, I was excited to see a health app offer weight gain as an option. However, EVERYTHING on the app stays set to weight loss despite what you put in as your goal. It‚Äôll send you notifications like ‚ÄúYou only need 400 calories to power yourself through!‚Äù as if you‚Äôre trying to barely survive. The actual calorie counter has a daily meter for how much you‚Äôve consumed of your daily goal. It fills up green, then when it‚Äôs full it turns red. Consuming enough or extra calories is a GOOD thing when you‚Äôre trying to gain weight, but this meter depicts the opposite. It even goes as far as to mess with your public profile & state that you‚Äôre there for weight loss despite the goal weight clearly being a higher number than the starting weight. I don‚Äôt see the purpose of offering ‚Äúweight gain‚Äù as an option when the entire app‚Äôs layout is permanently fixed on a weight loss routine. It‚Äôs extremely discouraging & fatphobic.

title: Can‚Äôt get past the name ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
body: It‚Äôs a pretty good app in all, I would like an option not to add ALL nutritional info, just calories (as seen on my fitness pal) because it provides a faster and easier option for many users, but the biggest block for me is that name... I previously used my fitness pal and had no problems keeping it on my home screen for everyone to see and I needed it there because I used it often and wanted quick and easy access to it, but having an app with ‚Äúfat‚Äù in the name on my home screen is embarrassing in all honesty. It was my biggest issue when I was looking into the app and I don‚Äôt know if I‚Äôll keep it at this point. I wish the developers would see common sense and rename the app to a more positive, normal name that focuses on more than just fat. I mean, think about what that does to the user. Each time they open the app they feel like they‚Äôre reaching toward a goal, but never reaching it. In other words, it makes me feel like I‚Äôm fat when I know I‚Äôm not. It discourages me and is off-putting, but more than anything it‚Äôs just frustrating that someone would make such a great app and name it something so humiliating.

title: Great app for tracking dietary goals
body: Whether you are looking to monitor calorie intake, or carb/fat/protein, this is a great app. I‚Äôve used it several times over the past 5-6 years, this time to track carbs. Also charts weight over time so you can track your progress. You can enter you foods by using the phone camera to scan the barcode, and most things I scan are in their database.

title: Most comprehensive app for tracking macroe
body: I‚Äôve tested 4-5 different apps to track my food and nutrient intake, including ones that cost money. FatSecret is the only one without annoying ads and is all business.

title: This APP is WONDERFUL‚ù£Ô∏è
body: FatSecret has not only enabled me to track my calories, fat, carbs, weight, etc., it has given me deep insight as to which foods are more nutritional than others. I am 73 and wanted to slowly lose 40 lbs. I log every bite I eat (no matter how small) + weight + exercise into this APP every day. My RDI is set for 1,400 calories per day, and this APP has enabled me to identify yummy foods that are high protein, low fat, low carbs, low sugar. With the adjustments I've made, I somehow manage to thrive on an avg of 1,200 cal or less/day, enjoy my fav foods, and I have yet to crave anything or be hungry.

title: Love the new iPad version
body: It makes it easy to keep track of weight and food.  I can easily share the meals across to my husband who is trying to loose weight too, but I did have to search hard for that ability. This new version makes it easier to keep unusual exercises/activities so they don‚Äôt have to be entered from scratch each time.  Kudos for that.  It‚Äôs also easier to move back to yesterday and add what you had for dinner if you didn‚Äôt the night before.  The sharing of info with HEALTH on the apple platforms is helpful since there is no blood pressure monitoring in your app.  Thanks for the hard work on the app, I used to prefer the desktop (and that should be updated) but with the new version the only reason I use the desktop is to share meals with hubby.

title: Finally taking some pounds off with a little help from my friend
body: I gained weight as I aged, went through menopause, had health issues and medication that causes weight gain. It was a loosing battle. After hearing so many people tell me I don‚Äôt eat enough and that is because I am NEVER Hungary I started using the app to see exactly how much I was eating.  Well my healthy choices I have always made totaled less then 600 calories a day!  So now I am sure to eat three meals and two snacks  I am able to get to a little less then 1000 calories per day most days. I am eating more protein and less carbs. Even being GF my carbs were too high. So I make better fruit and veggie chooses as well. That said I have lost 17 lbs in less then 2 months. Exactly 7 weeks.  It is coming off slow and steady and I am so much happier. I can start to look in a mirror and look at my reflection without disgust.  Love this app.

title: Overall very good
body: The layout is, for the most part, better than for MyFitnessPal. Some key things I‚Äôve noticed is that the green layout and the way the calorie numbers are presented make me less upset when I‚Äôve gone slightly over my calorie goals. My fitness pal makes me want to jump off the roof whenever I see that red negative bar at the top right haha. This is HUGE, because it makes tracking feel much less stressful and the overall vibe is much better this way.

title: I was fat and it was no secret
body: Finally got tired of tight fitting clothes and having a closet full of stuff I had fatted out of so downloaded FatSecret and started tracking everything I put into my mouth.  I wanted to lose 40 lbs in 4 months, and I am on track having lost 30lbs in 3 months.

title: This Is A Good App
body: I‚Äôm a Muay Thai fighter/coach, and marathon/ultra marathon runner, and I downloaded this app because I was switching to a high fat, low carb diet to train for my next ultra marathon, and I just need to be a little more efficient at using fat for fuel. This app has been extremely helpful in tracking my caloric intake as well as allowing me to keep track of my macro nutrient intake. There are a ton of foods already in the app, and if you can‚Äôt find exactly what you‚Äôre looking for, it allows you to enter the nutritional information for the food and save it. You can also enter any exercise and how many hours you sleep any given night to show how many calories you‚Äôre burning in a day, and what your caloric intake should be depending on your goals (losing, maintaining, or gaining weight). I highly recommend this app.

title: Easy to use; would like to see micronutrient information
body: I haven‚Äôt used a lot of other food tracking apps, but I‚Äôve really enjoyed how easy it is to use FatSecret (e.g. they list your most recently and more frequently eaten foods so you can quickly add them to your food diary). They are also responsive via email, which is really nice. Three things I really want to see: (1) a tally of all the vitamins and minerals we‚Äôve had for the day, (2) the ability to drop a whole list of food into a recipe (like some other websites) instead of having to add ingredients one by one, and (3) the ability to add ingredients to a recipe without having to create a recipe (e.g. without always having to add steps, a description, etc. since I often make the same recipe, but tweak it & also since many of us prepare our meals instead of buying pre-packaged meals)

title: This app really works
body: I used the fat secret website years ago to lose weight but the app is much better now than the website I remember. I used weight watchers prior to switching back to fat secret. I like the nutritional information fat secret provides and their database is reasonably complete with every type of food. I wasn‚Äôt a fan of artificial points and always looked up the calorie content of the foods I ate on weight watchers.

title: Great except....
body: I really enjoy this app and being able to track my calories, carbs, protein etc. the major problem I have is the app doesn‚Äôt know the difference between total carbs and net carbs. So for all you Atkins users and people like me who are blending Atkins food/snacks into our keto diet, I recommend you create your own food instead of using the search results. Otherwise the app will say you‚Äôre getting X number of carbs when you‚Äôre actually getting Y number of NET carbs. I would also like to be able to alter the stuff that automatically comes up. If you find Boar‚Äôs Head stuff, for example, you cannot alter the nutritional info. Which points you back in the direction of just creating your own custom food. Other than that this app is great!

title: Newbie but love it!
body: I‚Äôm only a week in and I love it. You can post on other peoples journals and they on yours. You can follow and gather followers, weight checks daily if you wish, easy bar scanner, can add your own recipes in and track every single calorie to know exactly where you should cut back.

title: Really good app for calorie intake and nutrition balance
body: I‚Äôve been tracking my calories and food on this app and I love it! My doctor put me on a 1200 calorie diet to lose weight. This encourages me to eat at home more and and track my ingredients down to the brand. Some brands of things are not available so sometimes I‚Äôll choose a standard description which is probably not off by much if any. It also helps me to discipline my eating habits. I enter in what I plan to eat before I eat it so that I know I‚Äôm not going to go over my calorie limit and to see if I am balancing out on fat, protein, and carbs. Most cases I want more protein and less fat and carbs. This app shows a chart that keeps up with this! This helps tremendously! Definitely worth the download!

title: Suggestion
body: Love the app, but have a suggestion and there wasn't an option for sending one in the app. It would be nice if we could put the time of our meals in. So you can set reminders for eating, water, or vitamins. Just setting a reminder time isn't enough because schedules change. Your wakeup time and subsequent breakfast may vary from day to day, as mine does. So setting the same reminder schedule isn't sufficient. This way you'll know when you last ate and can remind yourself to eat again at whatever duration works for you. I need to eat every 3-4 hrs or I binge. But I'll get busy and totally forget for 6, then it's a recipe for disaster. Or I don't consume all of my prepped food for the day, which is just as bad.

title: Worthwhile Effort for Weight Loss
body: I had reached a goal with the Keto Diet and wanted to find an app that would take what foods I input and give me the calories, carbs, fat and protein percentage needed to keep losing weight gradually while converting to the Mediterranean Diet.  I have been very satisfied with this app as I tend to eat healthy but occasionally give myself too many ‚Äúgreen lights‚Äù.  This App has made me think about what I am eating weekly.  I input my menu for the coming week over the weekend.  I shop accordingly and prepare overnight breakfasts, grains, etc. ahead.  I am eating more balanced and satisfying meals. I am able to see results both visually and physically and feel good while doing it.  I strongly recommend this diet.  Easy does it!

title: Excellent resource
body: I started using fat secret to count my sugars. As a diabetic, I have to be careful with refined sugars, carbs, and starches, and some things spoke my levels more than others. Using this tool has not only helped me figure out which foods are no-no‚Äôs for me, it‚Äôs also helped me lose weight. The menu planner counts sugars, calories, fats, etc., for me. I don‚Äôt have to think about everything. There‚Äôs a weigh in page to record weight loss progress, and even a spot to put in your own recipes for easy recall. There‚Äôs a community attached, as well- people there are helpful, make great suggestions, and just generally support one another‚Äôs journeys. Overall, I'm very impressed with this valuable (and free!!!) resource.

title: Best App Ever!!!
body: This app is amazing! It is so easy to use. I‚Äôve lost 7lbs in 10 days. I love how easy it is to look up a variety of different foods. It is also easy to add new foods. It will even give me nutritional value and serving size for my favorite recipes. It links to my health app so I only have to update one app instead of two.

title: Finally!
body: I LOVE this app! You can keep track of your calories without all the annoying ‚Äúreminders‚Äù and other useless prompts. I read some guy‚Äôs rant on Quora about how the only ‚Äúdiet‚Äù that works is one where you are in a calorie deficit DAILY. A üí° went off and since then I have been tracking my calories and try to keep below 1400.  I have been very successful at this even on vacation. I scrutinize everything I put in my mouth and constantly look for healthier swaps or ways to cut back. In 11 weeks I‚Äôve lost 14 pounds without having to kill myself with strenuous workouts. I‚Äôve had trouble losing weight most of my adult life but now feel like I‚Äôve beat that demon! üòä

title: User friendly & very helpful!
body: I did weight watchers for a while and I absolutely loved it. It worked well for me but I still struggled so I stopped, gained weight & realized almost a month ago that I wasn‚Äôt happy with how I looked and my blood work wasn‚Äôt where it should be for a 25 year old. I figured I would do something different and count calories instead of points and that‚Äôs when I discovered FatSecret! It‚Äôs so easy to use and navigate. You can scan barcodes and they have almost everything you could imagine. You can track your weight, track how much you‚Äôve eaten and how many calories you have left for the day. I‚Äôve lost 11 lbs in 3 weeks so this app is definitely worth a try.

title: This app is a lifesaver lol
body: At this point everyone knows that quarantine has affected a lot of people‚Äôs weight and for me it was weight gain. I finally decided I should start losing the pounds by ‚Äúdieting‚Äù first and realized after talking to friends I don‚Äôt need to necessarily cut off certain foods completely but just eat in smaller portions. After searching up calorie trackers online, FatSecret came up, I gave it a try, and now I‚Äôm genuinely committed to my health and my goal of weight loss! I haven‚Äôt stopped using it, and keeping track of the foods I eat while interacting with others in the social part of the platform has been a great motivator for me. Get the app!!!

title: Better than the rest!
body: I have used all kinds of apps to track my weight and what I am eating, but have always returned to Fat Secret.  Why?  Because in every other app I had to Google the nutrient amount of each food and add it manually.  Fat Secret offers the basic weight tracking and complete nutrition information, as well as a page where others share recipes and offer advise or congratulations, again without cost.  If you want more tracking it‚Äôs offered as a step up, i.e. water tracking, etc.  I have used Fat Secret for years and have stopped wasting money trying to find something better.

title: Very useful and easy to use
body: This app is great to be conscious of what you‚Äôre eating and exercising as well. The nutritional value of the food is calculated for you when you enter the amount you‚Äôve eaten. It is very user-friendly, easy to use and understand. Many foods have already been entered, and you can manually enter your own recipes to learn the calorie counts and nutritional information. By being conscious of what I‚Äôm eating, I‚Äôve been able to reduce my caloric input and I‚Äôve lost 9 pounds so far. There is also a feature where you can connect with others for encouragement and ideas and recipes.

title: Good system focused on nutrients
body: I really appreciate the focus on protein/fat/carbs and micronutrients as well. I really appreciate that you can fully customize all of those individual pieces! Not to mention the community of people posting is so encouraging! I‚Äôm still amazed that many positive people can be connecting on an app without some Negative Nancy‚Äôs. It‚Äôs easy to use once you figure it out. (Is there a video somewhere we could watch that shows you how to access all the various features? I couldn‚Äôt find the diet calendar that shows calories in/out for awhile). All I wish we could do is scan barcodes!

title: App‚Äôs Improving, but...
body: Fat Secret has improved so much over the years.

title: No nonsense calorie counter!
body: Honestly, the name of this app was a little off putting but I decided to give it a shot because I just don‚Äôt like the other more popular blue app to count calories. Fat Secret is easy to use, has minimal ads, recipe calculator/cookbook, recipes, community, challenges, browser access, food photo journal that you can choose to share with the community or not, and recipes, fitness tracker, a calendar to see which days you tracked and which you didn‚Äôt! It‚Äôs full service! It even has a service for adding your health professional‚Äôs email so you can send your data to them! It‚Äôs incredible!

title: Great tracker
body: This app is amazing‚Ä¶ You can track all of your daily intake‚Ä¶ See if you‚Äôre on track‚Ä¶ It tells you how many calories and carbs are in each item individually‚Ä¶ There‚Äôs recipes that are shared‚Ä¶ There‚Äôs people sharing comments back-and-forth‚Ä¶ It also connects to your active fit app‚Ä¶ Which all together you have reports to see if you‚Äôre staying on track and it‚Äôs very easy to use. I recommend it.

title: Awesome!
body: FatSecret has been an app I‚Äôve been using for 2 months now and it is extremely helpful! It helps me keep count of my calories and what I love is that you can scan the barcode of the food item and it will tell you how many calories and the name of it, it also has all the restaurants/ fast food places so if you eat at one of them, you can go under that fast food place and select the items you ate. The only thing I don‚Äôt like about this is (trigger warning) the option that tells you how many calories you had after purging, but other than that, it‚Äôs great! Definitely recommend if you‚Äôre on a diet or trying to lose weight.

title: Makes food tracking easy and rewarding.
body: This app has changed how I approach food. I know how to eat healthy but I eat too much at times and had no grip on my fiber intake. I have found real foods that I truly enjoy to snack on and it allows me to choose what food I really don‚Äôt want to let go of.

title: It‚Äôs Free and It Works!!
body: I started with this App a month ago.  I actually set up three Free Apps, ran all three for a week, and decided this was the most User-Friendly of them all.  It is relatively easy to look up the different foods we eat, the Charts it provides are helpful and informative.  It‚Äôs fairly easy to customize the amount of each food you‚Äôre using.  I don‚Äôt use the Recipe section but it looks impressive.  The single biggest opportunity, even though it‚Äôs a Free App, would be to allow us to choose our own week as opposed to it being Monday to Sunday;  that‚Äôs a bit of a pain albeit not the end of the world.  But that‚Äôs why I docked it one Star

title: Love the idea, hate some things.
body: While the plans and recipes are great, you are not allowed to access except through the App. Okay great, give me an option to download the meal plan I paid for, or the ability to copy/paste it for later. Having some ableness issues makes this difficult to use unless you‚Äôre using your IOS or google store product. Don‚Äôt say, oh get a big tablet so you can see it. I can‚Äôt afford a big enough tablet.

title: Super user friendly and convenient App!
body: I was looking for the app to be able to count the calories intake and none was working for me. Those I‚Äôve tried before were difficult to navigate and look for food I ate. This app is super user friendly, finds a lot of food and offers measuring in oz, grams, cups, prices, etc. It also allows you to scan a barcode and immediately returned the product you are looking for. It also offers additional meal plans for pay, which I haven‚Äôt tried but might in a later time.

title: FatSecret is a godsend
body: For everyone looking to chart calorie intake-review macro and micro nutrient analysis and record work out achievements-this is the tool for you. Amazing intuitiveness-reliable developer support and of course-the support of the online FatSecret community makes this tool a must have for anyone looking to improve upon their wellness. I couldn‚Äôt be more satisfied if it were free-oh wait, it is free.

title: Calorie Counting
body: I love this app, FatSecret, so easy to use .  I‚Äôve been 40lbs over weight for 10 years.  I thought I could lose weight on my own by just watching my food intake and portion control, but all I have been doing is maintaining my weight, not gaining any more but not losing it either.  Since using this app and actually recording my food and calories I‚Äôm a lot more aware of unnecessary snacking and actual portion sizes. I‚Äôve lost 5 lbs in 2-1/2 weeks, not a lot so far, but I finally feel on track to permanent weight loss and then maintaining my goal weight. Thank you, I love this app.

title: So great and easy to use!
body: I‚Äôve been so thrilled with using this app.  It‚Äôs allowed me to easily track my eating throughout the day.  Best of all, unlike a certain other app I had to delete eventually, FatSecret doesn‚Äôt have all of those annoying ads and hide their features away behind costly paywalls.  The library of available food is constantly growing (and I love making my own contributions) and I‚Äôm happy to see my weight tracked as I continue my healthier lifestyle.

title: Incorrect Information
body: I would love to give this so a 5 star rating. It is really helpful and I use it often. But being on a strict diet I need the information to be accurate. Far to often the information listed does not match the labels on the product. Case in point today I saw a marinara sauce where the label says 8g of carbs with 3g of fiber. The app says 10g and 1g. For people using a Keto/Paleo plan, that difference is significant. If it was possible to make the changes on the app it would be a great help. Also, using homemade recipes with information available for nutrients etc, it would be great to be able to add the recipes. I haven't seen where that is possible. Those two changes would make it a 5 star app easily.

title: Great app. The exercise calculator, not so much.
body: Love the app. However, the exercise calories burned calculator doesn‚Äôt do much of anything.

title: Excellent Calorie Tracker & Much More
body: Fat Secret has been a great app to help me lose weight by tracking not only calories but, macros by the day and week, add your own recipes, take photos of your meals, add notes to share (or not share) with others on the app, and look up recipes. I was a faithful My Fitness Pal user on and off for years until I did an update and they wanted to charge me to remove ads that I didn‚Äôt have before the update. I‚Äôm glad they did because I would have never found Fat Secret. This app is free. However, if I were to spend any money on a health app it would be this one‚Ä¶Fat Secret!

title: Great app and it works!
body: I love this app. After many years, I am a Weight Watchers convert. This app tells me every calorie I am eating and how many I am burning. I had a few questions along the way, but got them answered quickly by the support staff. I do wish that when selecting portions of an item that 1/3 and 2/3 was available to select. Many recipes call for thirds and it isn‚Äôt an option. This would make an already great app an excellent app. I‚Äôm 69 and it isn‚Äôt easy to lose weight at this age, but I‚Äôve lost 5 of the 15 pounds I want to lose using this app. This app is easy to use and addicting.

title: Comprehensive database and pretty easy to lookup foods
body: Pros: It was real easy to lookup both homemade, processed, and fast foods.  I liked the reports and visuals. It was free and without intrusive ads.  It was fairly easy to add foods after/during meals.  Good for short term nutrition survey or maybe serious calorie counters.

title: Fat secrets
body: This app makes it really easy to search and record food items for all of your meals. It also shows the calories and serving sizes for each item, which is great because you can eat various foods and enjoy all kinds of things if you keep the serving sizes under control. The app also helps you to keep track of all your food choices so you‚Äôre not just mindlessly eating and consuming endless calories. It has in app purchase available which I don‚Äôt use the basic app is good enough to log your food journal and help you stay on track.

title: Love the App
body: Been using this 1-year. I prefer it over the MyFit...Pal App because there‚Äôs No ads. This app has all free goodies.

title: Overall
body: Great app for beginners, has a lot of food to log and what isn‚Äôt on the app can be inputted manually. The interaction with others through the app news feed is also a great feature to keep you on track and updated with other users. Giving only 4 stars because not all work outs/exercise can be searched and sometimes the calories tracked per exercise per minute/ hour isn‚Äôt 100% accurate so jut keep track of your calories burned when exercising and manually adjust the number according to your accurate number.

title: Not Will! But Motivation and constant Change!

title: FatSecret

Please allow the same algorithm or formula to carry over to the charts and reports. With these types of highly POPULAR diets every carb and fraction thereof is crucial. Especially with the KETO diet. We usually try to keep our CARB MACROS around the 5% mark.

title: My experience with Fat Secret
body: I have used Fat Secret for several years now. I used it to lose 25 lbs several years ago via calorie cycling, and chose it because a calorie cycling friend was using it, it had lots of good features, and it was FREE. However, once the weight was lost, I stopped tracking the calories I consumed, my weight eventually rebounded, and I added some more weight, as well. Because studies show that people who maintain long term weight loss track calories, exercise regularly, and eat a low fat diet, I have returned to Fat Secret as a tool to help me once again lose the weight, and this time maintain it by tracking my calorie intake. My goal is to lower my set weight progressively this time and maintain it. I have already seen good early results after less than 2 weeks.

title: Work around for date problem
body: Here's a temporary work around for the date being behind a day. When in the food or exercise diary page where the wrong date appears, to get the correct one, select the "..." menu item at the top right. Then select "Change Date", and next select "Tomorrow", not "Today", which is already selected; you can also select the date for tomorrow on the date wheel below. By selecting the next day, when you press "Done", you'll return to the diary with the correct date now showing.

title: Useful and simple
body: I was looking for a calorie tracker that would record whatever I put into it, but this app does so much more. Not only does it do that, it also comes with a database to help me find caloric information on a wide variety of foods, plus it tracks activities (even resting!) and calorie burn. It's simple and I really like it. I haven't used the barcode scanner yet but so far I haven't had any problems. I also like the fact that I don't have to sign up for anything, it's an independent and free app. I think you can sign up for an account to get more weight-loss help, which is a nice option, but I don't like apps that force you to sign up for stuff. Also, as for the complaints about losing the Weight Watchers point counter, I don't know for sure, but Weight Watchers has its own app so maybe they complained because they didn't want another app using its trademarked info? Just a thought. I wouldn't hold it against Calorie Counter though.

title: Weight Loss Partner
body: I'm trying to lose weight and needed some accountability, and Fat Secret is my way of doing that. I track EVERY single thing I eat and am able to see exactly what I'm consuming. I can have a bad day and see what I need to do to have a better day.

title: Granny
body: Lots of good features.  Good lists on Restaurant items which is handy, but the one food item I need from Cheesecake Factory is the Lemoncello Cream Torte, and of course, it isn't in the list!  I tried adding it to my list, but haven't figured out how to add a food item without having to enter all the nutrition info, so I couldn't get it to accept it.  I only know the calories on some items, but it won't let me add the item to my list unless I add fat, carbs proteins, etc, which I don't know and haven't been able to come up with in a search.  I tried to guesstimate, and of course, it wouldn't accept that either.  Maybe I'm missing something, but I can't use this program unless some things are simplified.  It also needs smaller units of measure, such as 1/8 of a serving.  Smallest I've seen is 1/4 of a serving. Anyway, I would love to use this because the the good features, but won't because of the issues mentioned.

title: Can't believe it's free!
body: I was thinking of paying for the Weight Watchers online program when I saw a recommendation for this app, and thought I'd try it first since it's free. I've been using it for five days and so far I LOVE it. I especially like that it counts resting calories in addition to exercise, and the diet calendar keeps a running total of what you've eaten and what you've burned. Everything I've eaten has been in the database, and I've had no problems with crashes when using the scanner.

title: Amazing!
body: This app is so easy to use and yet it's got so much to it! I've only been using this app for 3 days and absolutely love it. You can scan barcodes of the foods you eat, adjust the serving amount, and take pictures of it too. It shows you a line graph of the progress you have made, as well as a recommended daily intake (rdi) of calories per day based off of BMI (not accurate but it gives you a starting point). If you don't have a barcode to scan then you can get a general idea of calories by searching "Bacon" which brings up different ways bacon can be cooked and treated with a general idea on serving and calorie sizes.

title: So-so
body: The UI for this app leaves a bit to be desired.  Often several dozen or more clicks to enter a single food item eaten.  They insist on painting food pictures on every screen which isn't what I need when I'm counting calories nor on a slow network connection.

title: WTH is wrong with the dates?!!?
body: I like this app a lot but a few issues: Wth is wrong with the dates?!!?? I click the drop box and click October 1, but then at the top, it says "tomorrow". No, Oct. 1st is today. Since update, the dates are off by one for every day in every year and idk why. I clicked Sept 8 in the drop box but the top border shows Sept 7th. So idk if I should go by the drop box or the actual date and today just fill in on "tomorrow's" food intake. Really annoying!!! Also, there are A LOT of errors in the calorie and serving sizes in the database. For example these cookies I ate were 2 cookies for 160 calories. However, the app showed 3 cookies for 160 calories. I've come across items that were just completely different calorie number so then I hve to say I ate 1 1/4 serving, even though I only ate 1, just to get to correct calorie amount. . Wish there was an easy way to send a note to company to make corrections.

title: 4.5 stars
body: I love this app. Been using it for a few years, and it has helped me tremendously with keeping track of what I eat. I have a few nitpicks, though, which is why I'm not giving the full 5 stars. 1) The columns. I want to choose which 5 items to see at the top. I can only choose three, since you've made calories and RDI permanent. I don't need those since I can see both on the opening screen. Let me choose all 5 items myself to truly customize my usage! 2) The cookbook. I LOVE this element, and use it every day, for my smoothies and homemade meal recipes. I can even guesstimate for restaurant meals when needed. BUT I would like a way to access it independently, without having to add a meal item or hit the search bar. This creates added steps I don't need if I just want to create or edit recipes. Just a direct link to the cookbook would be great! 3)...hmmm, I don't think there is a 3 for now! Keep up the great work, guys!

title: Longtime user, best app out there.
body: I've been a member of Fat Secret since 2011. When the smartphone app became available, I jumped right onboard. The database is so large I can't think of a single time that I wasn't able to find a food I'd eaten. I've tried My Fitness Pal but it's too cluttered and not as user-friendly as Fat Secret. I'm also a member of Weight Watchers Online, and I log daily in both apps. What's nice about FS is that I can track my weight daily whereas I have to wait an entire week to log my WW weight. There's something about having that daily commitment that really keeps me on point. I'm also a fan of the fat-carb-protein breakdown that you can see on the desktop site, so I wish they could bring that to the app. Since you can still see your total grams of each macro at the top of your food log, you can do the math in your head, but that pie chart is hot. ‚ò∫Ô∏è

title: Less clunky than MFP, counts NET carbs
body: Was using My Fitness Pal for years but every update made it more difficult to use for me, to the point that I stopped tracking. Got recommended this app by the LCHF/Keto diet community because it tracks net carbs at a glance. The app is attractive and easy to use.

title: Loyal fan
body: I used fat secret before it was a mobile app. I would log on from my computer. It has been helpful in my efforts to lose weight and get in shape (multiple times!). The calorie counter has pretty much all the foods I eat and there is a good listing of exercises. I use it on my Apple Watch as well. I do miss the communities-the social network piece that used to be on the computer version-maybe it still is there-I just don't access it from my computer. I would like to see this enhancement in the future: the option to enter all your food in the morning and then check it off throughout the day. I do enter everything in the morning now, but then the watch tells me I have 0 calories. Just a little thing, but would be nice. Oh and a water counter-so I can make sure I get 8 glasses a day

title: A great replacement for MyFitnessPal
body: I really like this app. It's a lot like MyFitnessPal was before it was stuffed full of ads and scamware. I only have two complaints. Quantities are broken down into quarters with no way to enter a number. You can't enter 1/3 cup something, only 1/4 or 1/2. To enter more specific quantities grams are used, which is not always convenient. The other more frustrating issue is foods are assigned a meal type and stick to that meal type when adding meals. If I eat something for dinner today the items will show up tomorrow in "recently eaten" but only when adding dinner. If I eat the leftovers for lunch I have to add all the items again from scratch under lunch. It's enough of a pain that I've started adding all meals under 'snacks' so it's easier, which is a shame because the breakdown chart is handy to check if you're spreading calories out evenly.

title: I love this app!!!
body: Before this app, I had to use 2 different apps to reach my goals.  I have been a Diet and Exercise Asst users for years on various OS systems, and I use iWatcher for points. I love both of those apps, but this app does the function of both of those. Now they add a barcode scanner, and I get to delete yet another app from my phone. This app very rarely crashes, is easy to use, and does everything. STRONG WORK GUY!!!  Keep it up.

title: Great App - One Request
body: This is a great app for tracking food intake and exercise.  The barcode scanner doesn't work on my iPod (4th), no big deal, I figure it was designed to work on the iPhone, so I use the keypad entry for UPC.  One Request - It would be REALLY nice if I could access my history of food and exercise within the app on my iPod without requiring an internet connection.  There are times when I want to check on what I've eaten previously, but can't because I'm not connected (which happens a lot in a rural area or on the road). An embedded notepad in the app would also come in handy for jotting down food and exercise when there's no internet connection.  I even looked for a paid version of this app that might have these features.

title: I'd be lost without this app!
body: This app is probably the only reason why I'm actually losing weight and keeping it off. I've broken my diet several times for the past 5 yrs (caused by lack of motivation) but this app makes it almost effortless to shed those  pounds. It allows you to keep track of your workouts and calorie intake according to your height, weight and age.

title: Flexible, customizable, better than similar apps
body: I tried several calorie counting apps and this one worked the best for me. You don't have to sign up for a website, but you can if you want too, which is a nice touch. This app has had all the different kinds of food items I have searched for so far, and you can select between various portion options (weight, volume, unit, etc.) which is convenient; other apps I tried only had cups of one food item, grams of another, etc. which is a pain. You can also edit your target daily calorie level or just accept the one the app recommends to you based on your profile, activity level, and weight loss goals. Simple and sweet! Try this app first and save yourself some time.

title: Skinnylinny155
body: I really love this app!  I can look up restaurants, all foods, name brands, & store brands.  It has a great list of exercises with the intensity of calories burned.  It also has a scanner so if I don't find the food listed, I can just scan the barcode to receive the caloric value. It also has an option for dividing the amount of a food. It keeps a daily updated count of calories consumed. The only thing I don't like is that when you enter your weight, it doesn't readjust and it doesn't show up on the graph. I would like to see that changed.

title: Update messed up some things
body: So this WAS my favorite weight loss app, and I was looking forward to it having an update. Of course something is always changed that ruins things. A minor lame change is the new look/design. But now, irritatingly, when you input an activity, the "remainder" of time in the 24 hrs defaults to adding TO either sleep or rest!! Ridiculous. So I have to keep trying to balance the activities back & forth so I don't end up with 9 hours of sleep or 7 hours of rest etc. What the heck?? Why not just be able to input the totals of each activity, sleep and rest included. Before the update you could choose what activity you wanted to add/subtract time from. It just doesn't seem as simple to use as before. Have started to look at other apps and I had hoped to not have to do that.

title: It works if you work it
body: A great calorie counting app. If you've counted calories (or fat grams, or any other food stat) manually, you'll love the ease of doing it digitally. FatSecret makes it really easy - tons of foods (including brand names) to chose from, adjustable portions, etc. If you can't find the food you're looking for, just google the food and fatsecret - there's often an entry from another country that will suit you. (I live outside my country of origin and this is a helpful feature for me). You can also save entire meals and recipes so you don't have to re-enter entire groups of specialized foods. You can also enter exercise. This is a great app to help you stay conscious of what you eat, which is a necessary first step to changing your eating patterns.

title: Awesome!!!!
body: This app is just full of awesomeness and what's not there, you can add!!!!  I use it everyday.   Highly recommended!!! I Guarantee you will love it!!!!!

title: Excellent!!!
body: I've tried many other apps but none seemed right for me. By chance I ran across this app. This is perfect. The food data base is ideal not only providing commercial product information (which I rarely need as I try to avoid fast foods and processed foods), but also has generic information as well. The photo diet feature is unique in that you simply take a photo of your food and the tech team will analyze it for you providing you nutritional feedback to use. That is amazing!

title: Macro percentages are calculating incorrectly
body: First, I have to say that I love this app and it helped me lose 65 pounds. But I have recently started tracking macros and there is a bug in the reporting that is figuring the macro percentages incorrectly. Protein and Fat values appear to be switched. This is so frustrating! I am still able to figure them by grams, which is more accurate anyway, but the percentages give a fantastic visual snapshot of where I am. Also, I would really like this app to go back to defaulting to the food diary page. I have absolutely zero interest in seeing what other people are eating. And finally, I'd love to see the macros, nutrients and calorie reports default to today. Again, I'm not as interested in my weekly values. They are nice to see, but I need the information for "today" all day. Otherwise, great app. You get 5 stars when all of this is addressed!

title: No one app is perfect.
body: I've tried several apps in this category.  Some are better at customizing portion sizes, exercise routines, or have a more extensive restaurant database.  FatSecret's entry isn't the best in any category nor does it have the "prettiest" interface.  That said, it certainly ranks well in every categories and when taken together, I feel it offers the best all-in-one solution.

title: Awesome!
body: If it wasn't free, I'd give it four stars because it's only lacking in ONE thing; just ONE!

title: Good App with a few design flaws
body: To echo other reviewers, it's amazing that this app is free! I have been using it since last February 2011 and have been very pleased. The weight tracker is my favorite part, but it is definitely glitchy. If you put in a note with your weight, it kind of floats around on the screen into the wrong place instead of staying under the date you wrote it. (This has never been improved. 8/1/12)

title: Needs decimal entry for food quantities
body: I stopped using this app for almost two years after my daughter was born. I come back and it is exactly same.

title: Valuable Tool
body: I've been using this app for seven months.  If you are wondering where the faults are in your diet this will show you.  I have lost thirty-five pounds this year, it's not a prison sentence, there are plenty of days when I reach the end of the day and there are still enough calories left for a small junk food cheat.  If you are honest with it, the app will tell you the truth.  Not always pleasant after a 1300 calorie All Star Breakfast at three in the morning and you discover you are at 192% of your daily food budget.  That is to say, it is a guide, a metric to measure, it doesn't do the work for you but it will give you a fighting chance

title: OK but no app support within the app
body: Did not really use. I could not find the wine ‚Äì if I have a glass of wine I have to be able to include those calories. The app does not include anything relating to portions. One should be able to go to pizza and add more than one slice ‚Äì without exiting and having to go back in and repeating. I like to use apps that have built in apps support and a place to provide feedback within the app. To me that is a reflection that the App developer cares about what the users think and also cares about improving the app. This is not the case with this app. There is nothing with in the app for support or feedback. I do not want to have to go back into the App Store search for the app search for the developer search for a place to provide feedback, etc. if they don't care enough or should I go through the trouble. Hence i am deleting the app.

title: Wanna love it
body: I am struggling to find an app that allows me to track/display macros and add food/recipes/nutrition info easily.

title: Great except for one thing...
body: I love this app.  It is easy to use and it has really helped me track my intake overall.  My only complaint is that I cook using Cooking Light and/or HelloFresh.  These recipes include all the nutritional information, but this app does not allow for me to easily add these recipes.  I have to create a recipe, which takes forever adding each individual food item.  This would be fine if I used that one recipe over and over, but I don't often do that when I cook with HelloFresh.  I would love an option where I could add my own item and the nutritional info.  For now, I just search for a recipe with a similar calorie count.  It's not totally accurate, but it does the job.

title: Exactly what I was looking for!
body: All I was looking for was a simple app for keeping track of calories and luckily I found this one. So simple to use and the perfect amount of features to keep from being overwhelmed.

title: So good is targeted by greedy patent trolls
body: I read recently that a notorious patent troll saw this company was very successful and so tried to blackmail them into paying for a patent so trivial it was just a joke. Thankfully the courts are getting better at punishing such ahole companies (patent trolls) and making them pay instead. All because this app is TOTALLY AWESOME!! I've tried many "diet tracking" apps and this really is the best. Not only because of the well design, but also because of the most comprehensive list of foods I've ever seen. Love the ability to customize and also submit new foods for everyone to use. Love it. One star off because of some problem with the "popular foods" list. Can't see pick anything from that list??

title: All this AND it's free?!!
body: This app is awesome, easy to use, has all the features I need, and the search finds just about every food item I could think of, even some store brands. Even if the search cant find it, it's easy to enter all the info and add it yourself. The only difficult thing is trying to estimate the nutrition info for home cooked meals. Overall, I'm happy with this app because it makes it so simple to keep track of my progress that it is encouraging rather than frustrating. One gripe however... The recipes don't tell you how much is in a serving, it just says one serving... Do I gotta break out a scale and measure 8 exactly equal portions or can you tell me one serving equals 1 cup?!

title: Can't use if you are too fat (and I don't know what they consider "too fat")
body: I was able to set up an account and add foods and track everything. First weigh-in comes along and I enter my new weight, which happens to be lower than my starting weight. A message pops up that tells me I am 'very heavy' and need to consult a doctor before beginning any diet. Thanks, but I already know I'm fat. That's why I'm on a diet! And my doctor fully supports my diet, for the record. I can hit 'save' but it just brings up the message again and won't save my new weight. Even though it saved my starting weight - which was higher!! Apparently this is for the people who need to lose 20 pounds but not for the people with more to lose. Very disappointed. I'm uninstalling this app and finding one that's a little more open to helping overweight people lose weight.

title: User Friendly and Free!
body: My friend turned me on to this app.  We are trying to be calorie conscious on the way to our fitness goals and The Calorie Counter by FatSecret has been very helpful!  It has a huge database of nutrition information and what isn't there you can enter in yourself in a snap!  The UPC scan feature is very convenient too!  All this along with the fact that it pairs an equally user friendly log for calories burnt during daily exercise and graphs and charts to give you a pictorial view of your progress in every area is a great way to see trends in your eating and activity habits.  Get the app.  You won't regret it!

title: Side by side comparison
body: Compared side by side with iTrackBites with in-app purchases, and I greatly prefer FatSecret. Note that this app is a calorie counter whereas the other is point-based. Wish I could get a refund for the other app, and give to FatSecret. Easier "one stop" search engine instead of searching multiple lists, manually. Either more food choices, or search engine is more intuitive; I couldn't find more items in the other app than found in FatSecret. And using this app, following their calorie limit, I lose 8 lbs in first month; for me this is a surprise.  I like this app and will continue to use it. Thanks for reading!

title: Great app, but...
body: Love this app! BUT...

title: Effective App
body: Using this app has given me better success than other attempts without any form of a food/exercise log. Tried side by side with MyFitnessPal & prefer this although either could work depending on one's personal preference.  Only complaint is that many food choices are set up from chain restaurant menus-probably food you DON'T want to eat on a diet; it's not always easy to find the healthier meals you're preparing at home. (Capability may exist to create home recipes-I haven't found it). Because of this get calorie estimates which may be +/-10% of actually, but in the long run the app helps keep you honest. Technically easy to use & have never had any glitches.

title: Best weight loss tool ever!
body: Fabulous app. Very useful. Very helpful. I love how easy this app is to use you can keep track of your weight, exercise, goals, and your food intake. You can look up each item you eat, whether you eat out buy something at the store and then fix it at home. Once you select it and indicate the amount you ate, it shows the amount of fat, carbs, protein, etc. you consumed and then you can see your totals for the day at the top of the page. It also show the percentages. I have FatSecret on my PC and am using the app on my phone and they automatically sync what you enter. Best tool ever!! LOVE IT!!!!

title: Missing info.
body: I have been using this for over a year and I love that it has no ads! Also, the interface is very easy to use. My 1 complaint is that it's missing alot of nutritional information for many food items. For example, if you are on a low-carb or Atkins diet and you want to put in a bun-less whataburger Patty there is no listing for it and only has the full whataburger.  I have to get out of the app, go find the information and then go back in and try to find something matching it manually in the search field. Also it doesn't let me save the meal for easier input next time. I am debating trying another app for this reason :/

title: I lost 20 pounds since I started tracking calories here
body: Worked beautifully for me and my husband. We tracked for 2 months straight while pairing this app with the Daily Dozen app (free) to make sure we were actually adding nutritious calories to our diet while reducing the empty ones. This app works pretty well and it lets you actually realize that your choice of foods is more important than just reducing the amount of food you eat. Exercise comes next.

title: Great, useful app!
body: I really like this app. I was previously just counting calories with my calculator, but this is way easier and saves all my information. Almost any food is found in the FatSecret system, and if you can't find a food you can do a custom entry. I am particularly fond of the analysis functions, which allow me to see how much carbs, fat and protein I'm eating. I can also track my exercise each day and my sleep habits. I wish that it had a function where I could count my own calories burned while exercising, the built-in calorie count seems to be higher than what my exercise machine tells me I'm burning.

title: Constantly crashes!!!
body: I LOVE this app ... when it works! The barcode scanner (using the cell phone camera) is hit or miss & crashes at least 10 times a day. The keypad function to manually enter barcode numbers (without using the camera) crashes literally every time I try to use it. This is extremely frustrating considering the searchable food database is limited. Other than the scanner there's really no way to enter foods that aren't already known in the database. I'm using an iPhone 4 - used to work great on my iPhone 3 & before the last update was released. I tried deleting then reinstalling but it doesn't help. Would be 5 stars if these issues were fixed.

title: Well done ... Best of 1/2 dozen apps tried
body: My goal is to count the calories I eat during the day and and track how close to my maximum.  This app does the trick.  Lets me scan in items that I'm eating prepackaged.  For cooking with a scale to measure the weights of ingredients, allows me to measure the amounts in grams and does the conversions calories, fat etc.  Possible improvements might include let me repeat the meal quickly ‚Äì when I have multiple ingredients it's a pain to have to enter each all over again.  And, let me pay you a few dollars more to get rid of advertisements at the bottom of the screen.

title: Love this app!!!
body: Im at that age where I'm going through the change. My metabolism has slowed down and I've put on about 17 pounds that I cannot get rid of even though I work out 3-5 days a week.  I now have the Apple watch and this app!!! A dynamic duo!! My watch tracks my heart rate, my workouts and do much more AND it helps me push myself a little more!! Combine that with your app which breaks down carbs, proteins, calories etc and accounts for calories burned .. And I have lost 4.5 pounds in 2 1/2 weeks BUT I am eating whenever I am hungry.  This app helps me keep my carb intake down among other variables!  I might get this weight off!!!!

title: Fat Secret Review
body: I gave this app four stars because I do love how you can track your food. But my only wish is too have a better fitness section. What I mean is having multiple options of what you want to record instead of just the time and calories such as reps and sets and the weight. But also to have a part were it tracks your steps/ moves if you are running walking or jogging. The last thing that I wish this had was a chart to show you how much of each drink you had consumed just like the ihydrate app. So if they consider my suggestions than I will definetly be giving them 5 stars instead of 4 stars.

title: Great app...but
body: I've used off and on since 2011. Tried others but always come back to this one. Couple of tweaks I'd like to see:

user_name: THE ONLY M IN THE WORLD
title: Amazing app!
body: When it said I should eat about 2600 calories a day to lose weight, I thought, "no freaking way." I found out that I was gaining weight because I was under eating and over exercising. Apparently a lot of dietitians have people like me come in. So since I have been using this app, I have lost 10 lbs but trying to eat that much calories sometimes is a hard thing for me when I work all day. But I'm trying! I've got about 15 more to lose till I'm happy! And I'm sure I'll be using this app for the rest of my life to make sure I stay on track. Thanks, FatSecret!

title: Fabulous!
body: I have never written a review before but this app is just too awesome not to.  I was diagnosed with diabetes and with this app I track total carbs, protein, sugar, fat and sodium.  There's other options available also.  It has name brand foods, restaurants and a barcode scanner.  It also has a wonderful website and great support if you need it.  There's just too many great things to notate but you won't be sorry if you try it!  I've lost 45 lbs and I'm still losing and my diabetes and high blood pressure is controlled!  I feel like a brand new person!  I will never be without Fatsecret!

title: Best calorie counting app by far and #1 in customer service
body: I've been using Fat Secret for over 2 years now and I absolutely love it. Works like a charm. Their reports are top notch, the customization features state-of-the-art and having a customer service that actually takes care of you when you have a problem is just out of this world, especially because this app is free.

title: This App is a MUST if you are serious about your health goals
body: I started using this app about two years ago. It was recommended to me by one of my good friends who also happens to be a personal trainer. Since I started using it, I've been more conscious about the foods I eat and their nutritional content.

title: good but needs a few features to be really great
body: first off this app has a lot of really good features that my fitness pal did not have such as a net carb setting and ability to share your entire food journal with someone. there are a few features that the app needs though to really compete with MFP though.

title: Crashing App
body: I LOVED this app before the last update!! I used it every day but now I cannot even get into my "food diary" without it crashing. I see that after the last update they now have an advertisment banner running, I wonder if this is creating network bandwidth issues. I do love that is it free but I would PAY for the functionality of being able to use it. I would love if the developers would give us the option to PAY for an app that does not have the advertisment banner. Also, I do P90X and wear a heart rate montior and would love if I could save my workouts for future use, just so I don't have to re-enter the data every time. :)  Please and thank you!!  Fix the crashes and it would be a 5 star!!

title: Works great on IPhone but not IPad
body: After 2 weeks I figured out how to get net carbs to show but wish I could have more than 4 categories to show. For those who want net carbs, go under the three ... at top right and choose your settings for display.

title: Very useful App
body: I weigh and/or measure my food to keep honest proportions. I love that I have the option of servings in ozs. vs. only measurements. There is such a HUGE database of foods but sometimes something isn't there and I love that I can add it. I love that I can enter recipes and get the nutritional breakdown. I love that I can memorize meals. I love the detail I get when I export. I love that my PC/iPad/iPhone are all in sync (most of the time)....LOVE this app and recommend it to anyone who needs something like this.

title: Useful tool
body: I have type one diabetes and use this to look up carbs to calculate my insulin. It is really helpful and the library of foods and brands is vast. The only thing I wished were different is the way things are grouped (or lack of) once you choose the restaurant. Like all the drinks should be together, all the sides, etc. If you don't know exactly what something is named or you put it in in a way that isn't exactly as listed, you have to page through to find it. Otherwise it's the best app I have found for being able to look up nutrition information for so many foods.

title: Easy to use
body: This is easy to use which is great because no one wants to fight with an app. I like that it's tied to the website so I have a choice of how to access it. Love the bar scanner. Some improvements could be made. It would be nice to be able to see your food or exercise diary for over a period of time. Or if you can do that it should be easy to find. Also it would be nice to be able to customize some things you track for example I would like to track the amount of iron I eat. But other than that this is a great app.

title: Really works well for me!
body: This app is really useful n easy to use. It will accept the barcode for almost anything. It gives all kinds of nutritive totals, so u can count whatever u want to, not just calories. I tell it how much u want to lose n it tells u how many calories to eat in a day, then keeps track of them for u easily n quickly. It also helps keep track of ur exercise n other activities. I've only been using it about a week (so haven't lost more than a couple of pounds), but I think it is super.  It tracks ur weight on a chart as well. Love it!

title: Outstanding weight loss app
body: I must say I never used a fitness app before.  A friend of minetold me to try this.  I did and hve been hooked since the first time I tried it.  Since then, I have tried my fitness pal, and thd fitbit app.   I must say as far as logging calories, meals, etc, I find Fat Secret extremely user friendly.  It actually makes being healthy fun!   This app is the reason I am changing my life.  I just wish this app would sync with fitbit.   Otherwise I havd not a bad comment to make.  I love it.  Thank you to the makers of this app, you have changed my life!

title: Simple and easy
body: I had been using this app for about a week and a half when I decided to try my fitness pal based on several friends recommendations. Right off the bat, my fitness pal overwhelmed me and I went right back to day secret. Maybe it doesn't sync with everything on my phone, but I like it's simple user interface. I'm also extremely impressed at all the food items in the database... Even my gluten free bread from my local bakery is on here!! Thank you fat secret for keeping it simple! I've lost 2 pounds in 10 days thanks to my accountability with this app.

title: A must-have for calorie/macro tracking
body: I find the app very easy to use. I decided to leave MFP and I chose FatSecret about 3 months ago after testing 6-7 different apps. Forget about the funny name, this app is a game changer. No ads, simple interface, and all the features you need for easy tracking of food, weight and even exercise (I don't use that feature, so I can't comment on it). The only thing that bugs me is that you can't scan bar codes when creating a recipe, so I tend to use the web version for this. I LOVE that every food can be entered in grams, as opposed to the tsp/oz/cups mess that was MFP.

title: Best I've used!
body: It's a great app! My only issue is that sometimes when I pull the app up or use the website, it's on a different day and I end up logging food for a day in the past, which obviously throws off my numbers. Once I finally end up pulling up the real day I'm on, it's blank and I realize what I've done, but there's no way to see what day or days I've been adding food to üò≠ If there was maybe an activity log or something that shows the last few things I've added and to what day, that way I could go and delete them and put them on the right day...that would solve this problem!!

title: Great App!
body: This has got to be the best app for counting calories, carbs, protein, weight or whatever!  The best thing is the fact that it has all the popular brands that one would actually be eating.  I have one request thou.  Being that I have an iPod with limited wifi access if you guys were to update the app and add the database to the internal memory it would make this app the only app worth getting!  You could charge $20 for this app and it would be worth it if you added the data base!  Without it iPod users are limited in many ways.

title: Good app
body: has a lot of potential but still not perfect.  It's really hard to balance your exercise time with what you're doing.  You have to reduce the amount of one activity when you add another...it's confusing.    Same with food...it might be easier to adjust how much food you've had if you can add it by amount (e.g. 1 tablespoon, 1 cup, etc.) vs. 1 serving.

title: Fantastic!!
body: This app is awesome, especially after using weight watchers' free app with limited functionality. It is not a weight loss plan, just a great tool for however you choose to track food, lose, or gain weight. I like that you can choose the nutrition info that is displayed as it relates to percent of daily calories (good for tracking net carbs on Atkins). Also, I've never searched for a food or brand that wasn't listed.

title: Latest update stinks!
body: None of my data will sync on my iphone since this last update. And if it does, it takes several days!

title: Used to Be Really Helpful for Watching Macronutrients
body: I used this app all the time!  It's the easiest to use on a mobile device, if you're watching macronutrients for meals.

title: Intuitive and well stocked
body: I used MyFitnessPal for quite some time, but I just like FatSecret way better. FatSecret does pretty much the same thing but it's more intuitive to me. I don't use any tracking tech (like FitBit, etc.) so I can't say how that would work. As a straight forward log, it's fantastic.

title: Best Nutrition App Available
body: I've been using this app for years to track my nutrition and I couldn't be happier with it. I'm also a competitive bodybuilder and without this app it would be so much more difficult to track what I eat. This app has pretty much any food you can think of in its food inventory. And if if doesn't you can always add one. My fitness pal or any other nutrition app doesn't even come close to this app. I would highly recommend to anybody interested in fitness or for any dieting purposes.

title: Keeps Me on Track
body: If you're looking for an App to help keep you on track, keep track of your daily intake, and be accountable to yourself, this is it! It's the perfect personal assistant for anyone trying to lose weight. It has all of the calorie information for thousands of foods, and it has all of the major restaurants, making eating out a breeze! The weekly weigh in also helps. It records your progress, so you can see how well you're doing and that helps to encourage you and keep you on track!

title: Great
body: Been using Fat Secret for almost one month and lost 3 lbs. but I work out running and weightlifting 3-4 times a week so I probably lost more fat than that. Living in Beijing so many european brands are not listed not to mention some of the asian food I eat so i do improvise a bit with my calorie counts. In any case this app really helps me stay focused and the results are showing. Hope the new update I downloaded will be as good. Anyone who is motivated to control their calories and keep high protein like me should try it!

title: Good app
body: It is a very helpful app. I have to google to find certain things on the app, things that I think should be easier to access. There is a home section where I see people leave notes for everyone to see, I can writes comments to their "posts", but I can't find how to write one myself (not badly enough to google it)) also I see people have profile pictures, at a first glance (and a second and a third) I couldn't figure out how to set one myself. But again, my main reason for using this app is to develop mindful eating habits, not to socialize.

title: Love it, but "fixed barcode issues" ? Really?
body: I love this app. and use it daily (although some of the exercises to choose from are unclear, and I do think it overestimates calories burned both at rest and in some of the exercises), but I am wondering (and can't find any info. on the site) about the claim that the updates have fixed the barcode scanning problems. I have iPhone 4 and the scanner doesn't work.  I think I got it to work a few times before the update, but now it never works. I hope they fix this!

title: Very good, would like to see some additions
body: I've been using this for a few days to compare how I like it to tracking in WW and it's pretty good. Love the scanning feature, but need to get creative when you can't find something specific. Would be great if it had 1/3 cup selection, vs. just 1/4 or 1/2. The choices for exercise is pretty limited, would be nice to have a feature that allows you to put in time exercised and level of exertion to determine calories burned as opposed to guessing that "cycling 15/mph" is the same as a spin class.

title: Best calorie app I have come across
body: The barcode scanner is my fav part. I made a grill cheese sandwich today and just scanned what I used and put how much I used of each and bam grill cheese with my ingredients. I also used an recipe from here and I love it low in calories and had all the ingredients. Easiest out off all. I have not gave up on using it because it Is an in convince like others I have used. Great app.... Thank you for creating it will recommend to all friends. And post on my Facebook as my fav app...

title: Version 4
body: I used to love this app and that is saying a lot since I have tried several different calorie counters on my iPhone.  Unfortunately, I don't like some of the more recent updates like the extremely tiny menu bar for recently eaten, most eaten and search when you are trying to add items. I always end up tapping the wrong thing even though I don't usually have that issue with other apps. I also wish the app had the option to put in decimals or at least 1/3 and 2/3 serving sizes as some of the other apps have. Positives are that you can change the columns of items you want to track and edit your own calorie ranges.

title: Neat, but search option needs help
body: I have only used this for 3 days.  The search option brings up far too many results that are not even related to the search.  I searched for an item yester day and it brought it up...searched for the same item today...did not show up.  If I search for Jamaican I don't want to see Mexican or any other country's food.  Otherwise it is simple and easy to use.  It just needs some work done on the search option.  I'll give it 3 stars now and when the search option gets simplified I'll come back and give it 5 stars.

title: Great, incredibly powerful
body: In previous versions this app was clunky. Nowadays its interface is smooth and easy to use. The real power behind it is the food database which continues to be incredibly extensive. If you want to keep track of your caloric and nutritional intake, as well as estimate the calories you burn, this is the best app on any platform for doing that.

title: Excellent food log(ger)
body: This app is easy to use as far as logging food & exercise. Highly recommend for that purpose. I do not utilize the community/social networking feature at all, so I can't comment to that. Only suggestion (& this is because I frequently get my healthy recipes from this source) would be to input the recipes from skinny taste. It gets frustrating having to enter new recipes almost daily - would be great if they were already there! I know it's probably not easy task.

title: Awesome app that keeps getting better
body: I started using this app in 2012 and in 6 months lost 15 lbs in a healthy manner. I realized I was just eating too much. There are so many foods in their index and if you can't find one you can add it yourself. Provides great summary of calories for the month and exercise. You can also sync with it on line so you can enter from your lap top, iPad iPhone etc.  If you want to lose weight or just monitor your carb/protein/fat intake and more get this app! Super app!

title: Does pretty much everything I want it to
body: This is a must if you're trying to lose weight. I love being able to so easily adjust the serving size of a food to put in my calorie counter, and it's convenient to be able to upload my own recipes. Besides minor, minor fixes, this does everything I want it to and more. Ridiculous amount of features for a free ad-less app.

title: A happy lady
body: I fist downloaded this app about 7 years ago and I lost 40lb. Over the last two years I gained about 20 of those lbs back (not eating right and not exercising) so a few months ago I started back with working out and eating right but also started back using this app to help maintain my daily calorie intake and just as before I'm watching my lbs fall off all over again. I love this app. Wish it had more recipe options within the app but over all an amazing resource.

title: Perfect, BUT useless on iPod when there is no Wi-Fi available!!
body: I really just wanted a simple app on my iPod to look up nutrition information for foods with specific portion sizes.  Initially, when I found this app, I thought I finally found the app to do this simple task.  However, then I discovered that this app only works when you are online.  If there is not Wi-Fi available, this app is completely USELESS.  What a bummer!

title: Works ok--can be frustrating
body: I love this app in that it is easy to use to log calories real quick. I don't love that it freezes up when I try to use the barcode scanner. There are also some things that calories aren't accurate. I have to double look sometimes. I have also had the app freeze up and delete everything I had stored which is really frustrating because of all the time I put into it. There was never a way to get it to work again I ended up having to uninstall it and reinstall it. Very frustrating to lose all of that data!! :( this has happened several times.

title: Most Extensive Database
