body: I've tried a few calorie counting apps.  This definitely has the best database. I wish weight tracker included the option for other stats (BF% in particular, which then opens up lean mass weight). Would be cool if, when you opened app,  it checked the local time, and had the current meal ready for input in place of "recipes" (i.e.it's 12‚Ä¶time for lunch), rather than tapping food --> lunch. Also would be neat if a user could check "prefill lunch with salad X on weekdays".  Best app for calorie counting, a few tweeks and it'd be unstoppable.

title: Good, but not great
body: Downloaded this app thinking I wanted to switch from another similar app which doesn't have a label scanner. I would like this app better if in addition to showing the number of calories of each type (carbs, protein, fat) consumed, it showed the percentage of each (for example, 45% carbs? 30% protein, 25% fat), the second thing this app is missing is the ability to build a recipe. But the worst part of this app is the ads. They do not tell you that this app is ad-supported and there is no option to get rid of the adds, not even for a fee.

title: Love this app
body: I really enjoy using this app. It's simple to use and allows you to scan items for quick entry. My only complain is that of the 5 nutrients you can check to show on the summary page, you can't uncheck calories or RDI. As my goal is to stay healthy, not lose wright, I could care less about either of those. I would rather show fat, protein, sugar and fiber. Please change those categories so that you can customize as you want!

title: Love the app!  Hate the name!
body: I was recently diagnosed borderline or pre-diabetic.  Had to get control of my carbs:protein.  Purchased a diabetes specific app and HATED  it-too cumbersome!  FatSecret is excellent and free.  I have diligently used this app and lost 1lb per week - safely and slowly. I'm not to my goal yet (I've only been using this for 6 weeks), but I've made more progress with weight loss than any other program I've used.  Great app-I've recommended it to several friends and family members.

title: Great app helps to track all factors to fitness
body: Mostly easy to input data and retrieve data.  Could use improvements in some areas. 1. Adopting new foods (sometimes this is difficult or impossible especially with unique restaurant foods) 2. Adopting more kosher brands.  This has been a challenge because even after I have entered a food not on the standard list it often can't be retrieved.

title: Used for a month. Love it.
body: Excellent app for both mobile and laptop. Journaling can be a pain and I've used myfooddiary and myfitness pal. This free app has good features like MFD. easy to journal. I'm starting to use the challenges which are helpful. It takes a little getting used to to get around on the small screen but the more you use it the easier it is to get around. I don't usually do reviews until I use an app for a while. Give this a try and Enjoy.

title: It Works If You Do
body: Pretty happy overall. I've lost almost 12lbs in 16 days just jogging, counting/restricting calories, and some intense but brief weight training. Fat Secret makes the tracking part easy, letting me focus keeping my discipline up. This app pretty much proves that (for most people, most of the time) losing weight is mostly just math and will power.

title: New to App - Great for motivation
body: I have been using this app for only one month, but it is the first time in 2 years I have lost weight, kept it off and am 100% motivated to keep going! I am down from 190 to 170 and have completely changed the way I eat by using this app's nutrition features. I have also started slowly exercising using the exercise logs, so many options that I can actually do at my current weight and health. Thanks for the motivation!

title: LOVE LOVE LOVE THIS APP!!!
body: Loven it love it! THe greatest And most useful app I've ever purchased. To

title: Excellent for food entries. Exercise part is awkward.
body: I've been trying to work in the exercise that I do, but I find it too complicated having to figure out the at rest vs. sleeping vs. activity, etc... I would much prefer just to put in my calories burned and have the app figure out the remaining cals for the day. Similar to the quick add feature for entering cals for food.  The rest and sleep can be a feature to turn on/off if you like.

title: Really great app
body: I‚Äôve been using fatsecret for a week and I really like it. Easy to use once you take a little bit of time to learn short cuts and what it can do.  Very easy to input items. I‚Äôve actually lost 7 pounds in my first week using it and am significantly more aware of my diet and nutritional choices. Have also used app on my apple watch - while functions are limited, it‚Äôs a great way to add items that are in your regular mix of foods.

title: In love
body: I am in love with this app! Def a huge diff w/counting/tracking calories. Keeps you motivated by keeping you alert in just how much you consume. Track your weight and save recipes or what you normally consume. Saves previously eaten meals and you can enter what isn't in there as well. Another reviewer stated it was glitchy and once in a while I do experience that but the pros outway the cons big time for me. This is my first calorie counter/tracker so I cannot compare.

title: I wish I could give it more stars
body: I really like this app.  It has a wonderfully supportive group to help motivate when you need it.  I love having the ability to scan barcodes to find products and the recipes and recipe builder is great, but you can only use the builder online. The one thing that would make this app fabulous would be the ability to sync with the website.  I use both because work doesn't have wifi but the app won't sync with the info I out in at the office.  I had to go online to finish out my day.  Super annoying.

title: Love it!
body: I absolutely love the fact that I can write in products not found in the database and save them; including pictures (this is especially helpful when you are traveling in different countries and you can save whichever product you consume). Can save meals and recipes, and even share them! It's a great app for tracking macros as it summarizes your total macros for the day at the top, tracks calories burned and weight loss or weight gain progress!

title: Used many different, but this out did them all
body: I have used many different apps, tablets, every kind of tracker out there ( well at least all I could find ) NOTHING has beat this one for ease and data base. I was a yo-yo dieter and now I can keep my weight off and enjoy life just by putting what I eat on my phone as I eat and stopping when I've reached my limit. Before I just guessed how much I had consumed ( not good ) I always went way over. This app is great.

title: Almost Perfect!
body: This was almost perfect for what I needed. The interface is great, not a lot of nonsense, very clean, good data summaries. Needs a much better database of foods and the memory on the search function isn't as predictive as it could be. I don't mind adding the food items myself, but it would be better to have something as robust as the myfitnesspal database. Although, I have found a few inaccurate food entries on both apps. I guess double checking is just part of the process.

title: Best diet help yet!
body: I had lost 20 lbs using a national brand diet, then stalled at a weight for two months. I found FatSecret and still am amazed at the vast variety of foods listed here. I have been able to keep accurate records of calories, exercise and sleep, and found that in order to lose, I had to eat about half the calories the national brand diet recommended. I am actively losing weight and feeling better week by week. Bravo, FatSecret, and thank you!

title: Best Ever
body: The only thing that ever worked for Me; made me conscious of everything I put in my mouth, discovering then how not to waste calories on a Godiva Truffle and have lunch instead. Kept track of consumption throughout day knowing how to plan if going out to dinner without exceeding my set intake of 1200 cals.

title: Overall great! Just a few minor bugs
body: It's really wonderful and has the easiest, most user-friendly interface from all the ones I've tried. A few fixes that I've noticed in switching from my droid, there's no adjustment for a horizontal screen flip and when you're selecting portion sizes they don't scroll through them before you can select so it can be hard to tell if you're picking "meat only". "Skinless", or something else like that. Overall great though!

title: Good app for tracking calorie intake
body: I like that I can be exact with calories by measuring food and not just by serving size.  It's easy to input home made options (once I use another website to figure out calories).  It does not sync with any exercise apps that I use, the barcode reader is not the fastest, nor does it always work.  Lastly, wish the color options were different - maybe I can change it but after using the app for 4 years I haven't looked.

title: Have used this for years
body: I love this app. I have used it on and off again for the last several years and it is such a user friendly and helpful app for those trying to diet, keep track of intake values, or track weight loss/gain. I believe it was the most recent update that gave you the nifty pie chart of fat, carb, and protein percentages; how awesome is that? Before I would calculate by hand. This makes following a low-carb diet so much easier. I would highly recommend to anyone.

title: Amazing
body: Better than MFP, in terms of content. Maybe not as large of a database, and definitely not as user friendly, but it really does the job of counting everything and offering personalization (a personal fav is the daily calorie goals) without charge. Could be easier to navigate, and I would definitely like to see a place for notes.

title: Comprehensive and uncomplicated
body: Current version has issues with what date it actually is; doesn't refresh quickly if I enter data from another device.  Otherwise, this app makes me want to throw rocks at every other system I've tried. Food lookups are fast and accurate with the barcode scanner, or the ability to add my own foods easily. All the right features for food and exercise tracking are at my fingertips, plus the nutrition breakdown (particularly macros and net carbs) really helps me see what to adjust. EXCELLENT app.

title: FatSecret was just what I needed
body: When I committed to loosing weight on a consistent, healthy schedule I went looking for an app to help me track my calories. FatSecret has been great to use once I got used to the many options. I wish it had a listing I could search of just the foods I have eat en instead of as it were the first time. It does let you search 'recently eaten' but recent seems to be too short for me. Thanks to the folks who make this service available.

title: Love this app
body: The hardest part of tracking all your health activities for me is ease of calculating food.  This app makes it super easy to measure calories or just what you eat.  In addition to that they have a great weight tracker, workout tracker and more.  Then to top it all off it does a great job of helping you visualize it all with great reports.  I was able to identify more easily where I needed to cut back on certain foods and at which meals.  I love this app.

title: Best Weight Loss App
body: For most of my life, I've been on and off diets. I've tried all the trends, many of the apps. This app is seriously the best I've used yet.

title: Fantastic!
body: This has been a great help in determining if I'm burning more calories than I'm taking in.  It even allows you to enter the ingredients from recipes and the servings to determine how much calories, fat and protein your getting and save that recipe for future reference!  It's a great way to track calorie and protein intake as well as track overall exercise (not specific weight training sets) but overall burn.  I highly recommend :)

title: Best of the best
body: I started out manually entering my nutrition and exercise in the diary. That was a good way to start because I could flip the pages back-and-forth to view the history. I tried my fitness pal and a couple of other programs before I found fat secret. Fat secret is by far the most intuitive program of it's type that I've used, simple yet quite informative.  This is the most used program on my phone.

title: Great app - extremely comprehensive food list
body: I've been a WW lifetime member for 3 yr and track my points all the time.  This app is a GREAT food list resource - it gives points for all different foods (VERY comprehensive list), and my favorite part is that it will do various amounts of foods - i.e. 1/2c flour, 1.5 c flour, etc.  Handy for calculating points for my favorite recipes.  Also has a very extensive restaurant list, which is extremely helpful as well.   And it's FREE!!!

title: WOW
body: I got this app late June and have already lost 13 pounds.   It's pretty easy to use.  Wish it had better "recently eaten" features.  If I have 31g of yogurt at breakfast I have to scroll thru and find the right amount if I'm using it at dinner. BLD&S should be just one big space, not so individualized.  My fridge and budget are only so big. If I buy a bag of carrots and hummus, I'm prob gonna eat that 8 times in 4 days, why make so many entries.

title: Great tool
body: I've tried a number of different tracking applications - this one is the definitely easiest.  I love that it easily tracks not only calories but macros, and that it breaks those down by meal.  The barcode scanner works really well, and if a food isn't in the database it's very simple to add a new one. I would highly recommend this to anyone that wants to start tracking their food and/or food intake.

title: Love this nutrition tracker
body: This AP is the best.  It is simple and easy for anyone to use.  I love the fact it has so many restaurant foods, even ones from the local companies here in Denver.   The vast listing of foods and ingredients makes tracking all the healthy meals I cook at home easy to do.

title: Good app.
body: I really like this app. However, set-up with the confirming email and syncing between my iPad, iPhone, and laptop wouldn't always happen automatically. It was a little frustrating at first. Tech. Support Doesn't respond very quickly when emailing for help. The food list and measurements are excellent. Customizing my plan has been pretty simple to figure out. I have only used it for a few weeks, so I will update my review after I have used it longer.

title: Great app. Has improved with Time!
body: I got this app as part of buying some books to help learn how to eat right and exercise years ago. It works amazingly well and many new features have been added since. Love this app and all the improvements!  Keep up the good work!  And yes, I have lost weight using this app.  Find the books. Buy the books. Read the books. Highly recommended!

title: Better than others
body: I recommend!

title: Can't believe it's free!!
body: I found the FatSecret website first and thought that was pretty great. Then I found the app and love it even more. I really can't believe it's free.

title: Love this app
body: This app is easy to use, I love the visuals to track my progress and I love how easy it is to find food as well as customize entries for my own serving sizes. It has a great food memory feature that makes t easy to find foods I eat often. Highly recommended to anyone just getting started in their journey or anyone who just needs to get back on track and more accountable to themselves.

title: Tracking for the tracking resistant
body: Fat secret takes all the guesswork out of tracking. From the barcode scanner to the seemingly infinite search capabilities, you WILL find the thing you ate. This is also coming from an exotic food enthusiast so you know I'm not kidding.  I love that you can break your diet down to the macro level even. Finally, I love that they offer recipes as well. It's one stop shopping for sure.

title: Great App
body: I really like the graphics. Very good looking app. I would have gave it five stars if the barcode scanner worked and I could keep track of vitamins and water intake. I have used other apps that do this but lack the large database of foods that this app seems to have. I also cannot figure out how to delete an exercise that I added for today. Can someone post how to do this? Also, where is a help file? Should the barcode scanner be working with iPhone 4?

title: It
body: I used another calorie counter app prior to trying out this one.  Now this is the only one I use.  It's much easier and intuitive and the barcode scanning feature makes it a snap to enter foods.  It's one of my most used apps.  By the way, missed this app a LOT during the temporary period where it was crashing.  The 2.0.1 version seems to have brought things back to normal.

title: Excellent App
body: This app is great to keep track of calories. Not only does it feature serving size, but you can change the number of servings you have and it will calculate that. It keeps a handy record of breakfast, lunch, dinner & snacks and you can use the iPhone cam to scan bar codes for food items not listed. And it keeps a record of recently & mostly eaten foods so you can add them to your diary quickly!

title: Very SMART app!
body: As someone who is steadily and slowly trying to gain weight, and keep track of the protein carbs and fat intakes, this app is fantastic! I use it throughout the day, and before I even eat dinner I know where I am on my daily intake. So before the day is over I can tweak my last few hours' caloric intake.  For example, I just got done eating dinner and I need to eat another 235 calories (of mostly carbs) before I go to bed.

title: Great but crashes a lot
body: My husband and I are both using this app to track ourselves for weight loss. Overall, we really like it- great user interface and very intuitive. There are a couple problems: 1) IT CRASHES A LOT causing me to have to input things again; 2) the options for inputting exercise are inflexible- there are lots of options but it would be better if I could create some or just enter calories expended ( maybe you can and I just haven't figured that out - so maybe it's not THAT intuitive).

title: Better but one more thought
body: Latest upgrade makes the app better, but still would prefer to have the summary total of consumed and remaining calories at the top of the screen, where you add food. That's the main info I'm seeking after food input.  Now I have to scroll to bottom of screen.  Would be better to move the fine detail info to the bottom of the screen for the folks who want that level of minutiae.

title: Really Useful
body: I use this every day. The app catches most of the popular/common brand names and is very accurate when comparing the calorie count to what the food packaging states

title: Mr.
body: This is an incredible tool to monitor and track macros and exercise.  I have used this app almost every day for the last two years, and it keeps getting better!  I am a fitness trainer  and use the fat secret professional online service with all of my clients. Provides outstanding insight and accountability for the trainers and the clients. Great job! Make a professional app so I don't need to use my browser!!!

title: Best I have used!
body: This is a great app that has an amazing database. The only thing that would make it absolutely perfect: if you could input recipe info and get the nutrition data and apply it to your calorie count. Right now I have to use a separate app for that and it's rather inconvenient to have to transfer the data. Otherwise this app has replaced my weight watchers app which I have used forever. Love it.

title: Love this App!
body: I found this app 5 years ago and I loved it then and I love this app even more now. I lost 25 lbs the first time and maintained for 4 years. I love the food database and how you can add food, find easy recipes and save meals you eat all the time. It sometimes has problems saving foods to your daily intake but not enough to annoy me. I would highly recommend this app to keep track of your calories.

title: This is the one you want
body: Syncs with the website, iPad, and igoogle. Extensive, easy-to-add-to database. The barcode scanner is sheer genius. Can customize tracking for dietary needs (like sodium or fiber rather than only fat, kCal, carbs.) Tracks calories out. Easily adjustable daily calories-in target. I cannot think of a feature it needs to add, and the interface is wonderful. And it's FREE. I would pay $5-10 for this, easily.

title: Fantastic
body: Fantastic app : easy to use, content. (Food lists), flexibility (add own food or menu or recipes). .

title: Love this app!
body: This is an excellent app to track calories if you are looking to lose weight, gain weight, or just monitor macronutrient intake! It is extremely easy to use - there‚Äôs a barcode scanner that allows you to scan in your food items with ease and there are even recipe ideas. As an added bonus, the online community connected by the FatSecret website is phenomenal.

title: Best food information app so far...
body: I have downloaded 4 other apps and they all paled in comparison to this. I have yet to search for a food that it has not found. In fact, there are probably too many choices of the same food packaged in different ways. But that's not a criticism. The information is detailed yet easy to use. Use it all the time. It is excellent. Can't believe it's free.

title: Easy to use and helpful
body: I've used this app to lose 20 lbs so far, and it's made the process so much easier. Almost all food I eat is in there (searchable by barcode too), and I can easily add anything extra.

title: Greatest for Accuracy & Accountability
body: This app will hold you accountable for every single item going into your body. The only way you will not attain your goals is if you do not use it or lie to it. I have lost over 24 pounds utilizing this app. The scanner and the saved meals make it easy to enter your data on a daily basis. I would strongly recommend to anyone trying to attain Health, wellness, and fitness goals.

title: One Simple Request
body: I absolutely LOVE this app. It's very simple, easy to use and tracks tons of great data, macro, etc.

title: Outstanding!!!!!!!
body: This app is crucial to my daily life. I am in the process of trying to lose 100 pounds & knowing exactly what I eat is paramount. The app is easy to use, very comprehensive, and I see it being with me for my entire journey as I transition to a whole new way of eating.  Furthermore, the Fat  Secret community online is very supportive and a wonderful resource.  I recommend this app to anyone who is serious about their nutrition!

title: Best App! Tracks net carbs!!!
body: I started a low-carb diet for weight loss and health improvement. I've been looking for an all-in-one app that tracks not only carbs, but net carbs, too ... well, here it is! FatSecret beats all other apps by a long shot (the paid ones, too!). It's free ‚Äì no subscription or paid upgrade needed ‚Äì and syncs with iOS HealthKit and WatchOS. Plus, it's highly customizable to track what YOU want. Your search is over!

title: Almost there..
body: I really love this app! I love how I can keep track of what I eat and the exercise that I do.

title: Fantastic!
body: Thanks to developer for making this application! I love how they set up and it's so easy. Before I go out to meet my friends last mins plan. I can look it up quickly on restaurant fast food chain i.e. " Chili's " and knew what I will be ordering for my dinner. It's very useful and help to cut down on bad fat stuff such as sodium killer and others hidden secret that we don't know. This is highly recommended.

title: Ads are in the way
body: I am trying this after being fairly happy with Lose It. My biggest complaint so far is that the ad band at the bottom is so tall that I can't use the buttons at the bottom of the app. I'm not sure how often I will have to use these on a daily basis, but during the setup it was very frustrating. Yes, I understand the need for ads on free apps, but the ads should not interfere with being able to use the app.

title: Sweet app
body: I've reviewed several calorie counter apps and this us the best one. Easy to use, nice features, accurate, and convenient navigation. I can track my calories and carbs in one place, log my activity level, or quickly look up a food (including national, chain, or store brands) before making my decision. If a food is not on the very thorough list, I can add it myself. Love this app! Great job.

title: Love it!!!
body: The only thing I wish it had is body measurement tracking. When I'm not losing weight, tracking my inch loss is a great motivator. I love the simplicity of the app. I've spent quite a bit on fitness apps and this FREE one will be my favorite. Will still have to use another for inch loss thoughÓÅò   I really love that it has activities in addition to exercises, like resting, driving, sleeping. It's like having a bodybugg/gowear fit without having to pay the $200. Thanks !!!

title: Love it but could use some adds
body: I really love this ap, it has an esthetically pleasing interface with the date and summary. A few features I would love to see are:

title: Great app; excellent use & low crash rate
body: I've used the website for this (fatsecret) for 6+ years. The app is a great addition, although I didn't sync it because I didn't want to lose my historical data. Not sure why it couldn't merge the two. The app is great for daily logging of food and goals. Would be nice if it had food group categories to slot food into though. Overall it's very good. Only crashes when canceling barcode scans.

title: Great weight/food app tool
body: I find this Fatsecret app very helpful for finding out nutrition info on a wide variety of foods and brands. The barcode, a great added bonus. Just punch in the barcode digits and it finds the item. I absolutely love that you can vary the serving size that you need, from the smallest of amounts to the number of servings, accordingly. A must app if wanting to keep track of all your weight/foodie needs.

title: Love this app!!
body: I have been using this app for years and I love it!  I love how quick and easy the scanner for UPC's is. My only recommendation for an improvement would be able to add the time that you eat your meals/snacks and maybe add a body measurement section, that way we don't always have to rely on the number on the scale to determine the changes in our bodies.

title: Best App Ever!
body: I am on a weight loss program that, if you can believe it, does not have an App!  I have to keep track of my carb intake so when I was searching for an app to help me I found Fat Secret and installing feel in love! It has everything I need AND I enjoy using it, user friendly, has all the foods I am looking for, the scanner is wonderful and just love the format!!! Keep up the great work!

title: Fat Secret
body: Great app, very user friendly and love that it tracks your protein, fats and carbs. Great barcode scan to quickly add products. It works if you track! This app was recommended to me by my doctor and I highly recommend over the weight watchers app I was using prior to this app cause I have to pay attention to carbs, protein and fats as well as calories so I make better choices to stay in my range.

title: Great Program
body: I am very happy with the functionality of this software and the support from the developer. It's superior to Lose-it, because of the  robust food database,barcode look up feature and the website community. my only suggestion is to add a daily goal and real time under/over status as compared to each person's caloric requirements.

title: Could not recommend higher.
body: I'm down 100+ lbs while using this app. over the past 14 months. No way around the fact it works and it's flexible. I have it everywhere to keep it convienent (iPod, BlackBerry, Laptop, wife's Droid) so I have no reason not to keep up with the number of calories I'm consuming. By far the best app. I've ever used on my iPod, paid or otherwise.

title: I love this app! Better than ones that cost money
body: This app is way better than the live strong app. My only recommendation would be to include more exercise options or at least more specific. For example elliptical as an option, instead of exercise machine. I love this application. They have the nutritional information of everything and every brand.

title: So simple to use
body: I have been using this app and the website to track my calories/workouts/weight for over a year now and I really like it. I find it very simple to use which is perfect for me. I don't like a lot of unnecessary bells and whistles that i will never use. It is straight forward and I love how now they have incorporated recipes with the calorie counts already done. Really great app

title: BEST FOOD DOC APP
body: I live Fatsecret.  Whenever I need to lose weight or see what a serving of one of my recipes' nutritional info would be, I use Fatsecret.  I still like the full web version a little better, but the app is great when i just need to add food items quickly.  Takes some getting used to and time to enter new foods and recipes, but once they're in there, you've got 'em!  Great tool.

title: Restaurant, brand and market sections are great
body: I have used my fitness pal and my plate and both are  excellent. BUT  I stumbled on this, yesterday had haven't really tested it. BUT to a first cut, the section on chains, supermarket, and brands is excellent and maybe more comprehensive than the competitors. Is certainly easy and quick.  Try it and you will probably enjoy it a lot for the simplicity The detailed food tables.  SIMPLE QUICK AND COMPREHENSIVE ESPECIALLY THE CONMERCIAL PARTS OF THE TABLES

title: Wife and mother
body: I am glad that I downloaded fat secret. It's a great tool to see how to hit your caloric intake goals. Also Obama able to see trends and patterns in my eating habits that I might not see if I wasn't keeping track. For example I ate a lot more snacks which added quickly to my caloric intake. It helped me see the value in not eating fast foods and more at home meals. I am glad and support fat secret .

title: Better than MyFitnessPal
body: I have used my fitness pal and fat secret. Fat secret is easy and focused. It has The gif diary, weight and exercise tracker, reports, etc. The interface is simple, clean and clear. The new version of MFP is busy, it has too many distractions and too much extra stuff. I really like this app because it is helping me stay focuses on what's most important for my weight loss.

title: Easy, Fast and very helpful
body: One of the few apps for weight tracking that makes complete sense and easy enough to pop in, search and record.  I'm truly enjoying the fact that most of the foods I eat include brand names and breakdowns of all nutritional info.  Thanks for this app.  I'm much more confident that I'm consuming and staying in check with my goals.

title: Net carb tracking
body: Still the best app for tracking Net Carbs in my opinion, with no extra purchase to do so, or elaborate work arounds or tweaks.

title: wanting/wishing
body: I love this program for its possibilities!  It is great as is, when it is not closing without notice, usually while you are trying to enter the food in your diary.  I do however, wish that I could do substitutions. (example.. hamburger helper-- we make ours with ground turkey and fat free milk, but the calorie count is as prepared with beef and skim milk. I also wish that when counting fat grams that I was able to view good fats vs. bad fats.  It lumps them all in together.

title: wonderful app but . . .
body: The scanner feature is wonderful, however it keeps crashing or timing out not sure what is going on but it is very frustrating to get kicked out right in the middle of inputting information. This is the only complaint I have otherwise the app is a wonderful tool to have. I will give it 4 stars but once the bug is fixed on the crashing it would be perfect.

title: Love it!
body: Love this app!  I haven't found a single restaurant or food choice that isn't in the database.  It allows you to type in the UPC if it can't read the barcode.  And it has found every food I've tried so far.  I love the diet diary!  You can set how many calories you want to net in a day and get a visual reference of how you're doing.  I would pay for this app- I can't believe it's free.

title: Some issues, but hey it's free!
body: Downloaded a while ago, finally started to use it and I can't believe how GREAT it is...sure, barcode crashes, but I'm just happy it has that feature, I'm sure they will fix it...so far it has helped me tremendously for five days.  I can't afford weight watchers right now so this app is awesome for me!!  Plus I've hated points since they started them!!!

title: Good App but.....
body: I enjoy the features BUT it crashes or bogs down often, in the "weight tracker" section the "goal weight" won't change from the intial setting of 175 that I put in a few months ago. I have a new goal weight that I'm trying to achieve that's lower than 175. However, everyday when I weigh-in and input my daily weight and try to input a my new goal weight but it never takes. I emailed the operators  but no updates yet.  I recommend another App until this one gets updated.  Otherwise, it has potential.

title: Best Calorie Counter App
body: Very simple to use, easy way to track my diet and exercise. I've recommended this app to my friends. I wish they would add more exercise options, it's not bad or anything mostly everything is already on there. But I use the elliptical trainer everyday and its not on the list.  I use the "other" option instead. But it's been awesome so far!

title: Easy, convenient way to track progress!
body: I've been using this app now for five months, and it's easy and convenient enough that I can honestly say I've used it every day and incorporated it into my daily routine. Adding calories and exercises is fast and easy. AND it's free! Highly recommended. Not every brand of every food is stored in the app, but there's usually a good approximation for whatever it is you're eating.

title: Very Helpful
body: This app is instrumental to my success in following the LCHF eating plan. I am able to keep carbs below 50 g per day and have even attained 20 g per day utilizing this app to plan meals and track progress. Love some of the low carb recipes too. This way of eating is so contrary to the last 30 years of advice for low fat diets that this app has been a major contribution toward my success.

title: Awesome app!
body: This app is awesome! It truly has helped me keep a diary of what I'm eating and helping me keep track of my macros! As I'm trying to build muscle, I know exactly how much protein I'm consuming in the day! I recommend it to anyone that's trying to keep track of their macros, loose weight and just hold yourself accountable for your nutrition intake! It works if you're committed! Oh...helped me loose 7 lbs too! üòÉ

title: Helping me lose weight...
body: This app is definitely helping me lose weight by allowing me to track my calories and see exactly what I'm eating throughout the day and adjust accordingly. It's amazing to see how much you actually over eat when you don't count calories...this app is easy to use and will help you achieve your goal if you stay consistent

title: It needs wifi connectivity :/
body: OK, first, I've got to say this is an awesome calorie counter! I use it everyday. You can look up hundreds of foods, and if you can't find something, you can always add it to the app. One thing I don't like, is that it requires an internet connection! I really hate the fact that when your somewhere w/o wifi, it says "Requires internet connection" or "Network timed out". Please add an Offline Update?

title: Pro version please
body: This app has helped me to make a significant lifestyle change. For that it (they) have my endless gratitude. I would love a pro (paid) version which would include weekly, monthly, and yearly intake and output charts. The ads in this free app are very unobtrusive but a paid, ad-free version would be awesome!

title: Best App, Worst Name
body: I love tracking my calories. It's really shown me where I blow it & has given me inspiration & motivation to continue eating healthy. I'm goal driven & this helps motivate me like nothing else ever has. Only small complaint is that I often cook from scratch & this is challenging to input correct numbers with those kinds of meals, especially if there's a lot of ingredients.

title: Great!
body: I love this app. I was using MyFitnessPal for over a year but didn't find it as easy. When I started at a weight loss clinic in July, this app was one that was recommended to use. I loved it from the first time I used it. It's simple, tells me exactly what I want to see for each meal-ie carb count, protein grams. This makes it so much easier to see where I stand for each day.

title: Really Good
body: I have been using this app for about 2 weeks. It is starting to make me see my bad habits from eating and lack of sleep. It takes about 1 week of logging everything so that you develop a view of your eating and exercise, and sleep routine. I plan on using this app everyday to help me reach my goal of losing and maintaining my target weight.

title: Easy and Functional
body: I love this app, so much that I had to give it a positive rating (which I rarely do). It's so simple to track my meals, weight, and even exercise. I love the customizable database where i can choose which macros I want to monitor. Also the ability enter information via barcode is super convenient. I would recommend it to anyone.

title: So helpful!!
body: I never have been very big on diets but I also didn't realize how much I eat how many calories over what I need that I eat this app just help me realize how unhealthy I was eating and I'll actually pause before eating something and look at the back and type it in to see if it's going to put me over for the day so awesome I love this app

title: Keto/Macro friendly
body: I was looking for an app that I could input my macros into, I tried at least 4 other apps and none of them include everything that FatSecret does! MFP is supposed to, but it is not as user friendly as FS is, I easily modify my macros to my weight loss in order to keep me on track.  I've been using this for 4 months now and couldn't be happier üòÄ.

title: Fastest, easiest and BEST!!
body: There are so many apps out there to journal your food, exercise, etc. Fat Secret is so easy to use! The best part is that you can immediately see how many grams of carbs, protein and fat you have consumed for the day. Once I hit my carb limit, then I stop eating. Also, just scan your food as you are preparing it so it makes journaling fast, easy and fun!!

title: Gets the job done
body: For me, the secret to losing weight is remaining aware of my intake. I was using another app, but they got greedy, LOADED it with ads and asked too much money to make them leave. So I dropped that one. Didn't use one for a while ‚Äì gained a lot of the weight back. Got this one, works just as well as the last one. I hope they don't get greedy.

title: Awesome App!!!
body: It's one of the few apps I had to have when I converted from Blackberry to iPhone. Best of all, it's even easier to use on iPhone! All my data even came with me through the sync feature, which syncs across devices and the website, so no matter where you're inputting data, you're always up to date!

title: Amazing accurate
body: The "Fat Secret" application is the best I've ever seen. It have every single food and brand in its extensive database allowing for complete Accuracy when logging food & activity. You won't be disappointed in downloading it. Thus far I've lost 5 pounds in two weeks from tracking and logging my meals. I highly  recommended it.

title: Great app to track calories
body: I used to use MyFitnessPal, but found I had to upgrade to premium to do what I was able to do before for free. FatSecret is easy to use and has a large library of food and exercise making it easy to track. I've already lost 6 lbs toward my goal, and this app has definitely helped.

title: What an amazing app!
body: This app has truly helped me change my lifestyle and track my healthy eating.

title: Pretty good, few complaints
body: Simple, clean, to the point. I love it. My only complaint is that the fractions and units available to use aren't as user-friendly or precise as I'd like (Can't type in decimals, have to use drop-down list of fractions, but only 3 fraction options available. And for some foods, the only unit is 1 serving. So instead of entering that you ate 5 crackers, you have to say you ate half of one serving of 12 crackers.)

title: Great little diet app
body: I've used Fat Secret off and on for over 4 years and like it a lot. It's great for tracking your diet, exercise, and weight. I use the app to maintain a diabetes-healthy diet and to track my daily carbs. I like how Fat Secret partners with the Apple Health app to track all kinds of things.

title: Great for tracking key stats
body: I mostly track weight, calorie intake, and calorie output. From that perspective it is a fantastic, easy to use app. I love being able to scan the barcode of packaged food. Entering a home made meal from whole foods is more time consuming but still a simple process. I'd love to see the food library expanded even more.

title: SusyQ
body: Enjoying this app. Very simple and easy to use. It has all the basics that you need to get started toward your goals. It really puts you in check on what you're eating and what a true serving size really is! When you start keeping track is when you realize how much you consume on a daily basis. I would deff recommend this app.

title: Excellent
body: Love this app just about anything you can think of regarding food is in their database. Simple and easy to track your meals. Only things I could think of that would make the experience better is more types of tracking i.e. BMI, body measurements, and A simpler way to make your own recipes to store them for future use.

title: Needs flexible name/number of meals
body: For the most part I like this app. Personal trainer had me download it so she could track my progress. I work an odd schedule and I eat breakfast at lunch or dinner at breakfast time. I would like to have the option to rename the meals to times like myfitnesspal. Or even to add more meals besides B/L/D and snacks.

title: Suggestion
body: I really like this app and all of the options. For the list of exercises you should really add a yoga and stair option. Thanks also I was keeping track of my breakfast and I had sausage links I had 1 and 1/2 and you have it in there as 3 for the serving size and no way to adjust now I have to remember to knock off 130 calories because I didn't eat the whole serving size.

title: Latest updates downgrade app
body: Doing nothing to software is often better than doing something.  Such is the case with the latest update. Spin wheel choosers are almost unusable.  Look and feel are not intuitive.  This app doesn't have to be pretty- it HAS to be functional.  I really liked the old look and feel.  If you must change for iOS 7.0.x at least change in favor of usability and content.

title: Why isn't this more popular?
body: I love this app so much. It's more user friendly than myfitnesspal, it has an easier to find and larger food bank than lose it. The exercises could be expanded but it's easy to find something in the same calorie burn range if you don't do a normal workout. I recommend this to EVERYONE.

title: Best counter I've used!
body: I have used all kinds of different apps to count calories and different ones to record my work outs! I love that this one does both!! I have yet to find something I don't like about it! It's easy to use, I have used it everyday since I started watching my diet and doing more exercising! Love, love, love this app!

title: Good app, but with one flaw
body: This app is great, easy to use, and simple. The only problem I have is that the in-app RDI calculator is pretty terrible. It estimated I needed to eat about 2800 calories a day to lose weight; I checked with other websites after about a month and found out my RDI to lose weight is about 1400 calories. So pretty big flaw for someone who relies on using the in-app RRI. Besides that problem it's a great app.

title: Keeps me on track.
body: Even though i was eating paleo diet and working out, i was not losing as much weight as i wanted to.

title: The Best
body: This is the best calorie tracking app I've tried. The color scheme, app layout, and graphing elements are the most user friendly.

title: Please add...
body: A) Ability to track motion from phone (using isteps, etc)

title: Great app for tracking progress!!
body: Love all the foods they already have in the database. Really makes logging foods so much easier! Would love to see them give you the option to set your macros at target numbers instead of only setting calories - would help with Atkins and Keto diets as well. Overall the best food and weight tracking app I have been able to find.

title: Best way to keep track
body: Fat secret had always been my go-to place when it comes to dieting and keeping track of your weight. Unlike other weight trackers, fat secret actually has a huge selection of name brand foods and stuff people actually eat so you are able to log pretty much anything you eat.

title: Not a Flexible Platform
body: I liked this app a lot until I tried to add some food from the cafeteria at work. I don't know any information for the food (it's from the salad bar) so I have to guess. It's impossible to enter this food into the journal! You have to know exactly how many calories, carbohydrates, protein, and fat are in the food or you can't record it. I don't know! I just want to guess the calories. Try Lose It! That app is more flexible.

title: How this app works for me
body: At first i added this app and lost 28 lbs but i figured it was just me since i felt like i never really used the app. So i deleted and ever since then ive stayed the same weight and i was like honestly what an i doing wrong. But after that i added the app again and lost 10 more lbs so i believe the app works for me!

title: Indicator bar
body: This is an awesome app. It would be cool of the app incorporated a indicator bar much like one that tracks cell min history thought a month. Only this indicator would track your caloric intake daily. I am trying to gain weight and It would be really nice to see my progress  throughout the day to see if I'm ahead of my target or behind.

title: AWESOMENESS!!!
body: This app has been absolutely essential in being a part of my 80 lb + weight loss! It is easy to follow and track and has such a variety of foods. The scanner works great and the whole interface is fun to use. I actually look forward to when I can next record! Thank you so much for such an excellent app!

title: Best weight management app ever.
body: As I decided to lose weight, I didn't sure whether ate too much or not. Fatsecret actually shows me how many calories I ate, and I found out that I ate too much.

title: Decent
body: The app is pretty user friendly. I'd like to see servings in decimal instead of fractions. Also I'd like to see much more of my weight history. I've been using this app for almost 5 years now and have a lot of data that id like to export to other apps. All in all it's pretty good but there's much more I'd like to see. I'll start looking elsewhere until they integrate health kit.

title: I love this app!!!!
body: I was diagnosed with type one diabetes three weeks ago. My friend told me about this app and I love it!!!! I can keep track of what I eat and how many carbs I consume. I really love that it shows restaurant menus so I can plan what I'm able to eat before I get there, including the carbs and sugars. I would highly recommend this app.

title: Very thorough app!
body: I've been using this app for a couple of months now along with the app for nutrisystem since I've been on that program. This app is great. I'm able to even search for the nutrisystem meals and they're all in there. I love being able to track fat grams and calories as well as other nutrients. I like it!

title: Great App
body: This is a great app, though the design could be better. It's not necessarily completely outdated nor flat-out ugly. However, it's not necessarily top-quality design.

title: Lost 10 pounds in 4 weeks
body: At first it was a little confusing but when I got the hang of it I was able to track everything I eat the calories and even the calories I burned with exercise... this app is great... o already lost 10 pounds just by eating right and still going down... I recommend it

title: Great, but big bug
body: This is a great app, the only one I've actually rated. However, there seems to be a bug with the barcode scanner; it'll scan the UPC (or I type it in), it'll pull up the info, then freeze. It doesn't matter how long I've waited thinking maybe it just processing data, but it stays stuck. Fix that and it'll be 5 stars, hands down.

title: Complex, featureful, deep food list
body: Doesn't follow the typical Apple iOS guidelines so it's a little bit odd looking/feeling. Lots of buttons and confusing layouts. Don't like switching between diet and exercise calendars. The calorie tracker doesn't calculate what I think my RDI is. Ad's are annoying. Online sync is cool but not great. Love the huge online DB of foods. Barcode scanner is a great feature but it crashes the application! LoseIt is another great free application but it's missing the barcode scanner and massive online food library.

title: Mostly Great
body: I love the app. I enjoy the tracking. I really like that it syncs up online so my other iProducts are up to date. I like the exercises tracking. I'm bummed that the barcode scanner doesn't work for me. I just input the number by hand and all is well but it could save some time and frustration.

title: Instrumental in my fitness
body: Best overall tracking app I've found.  Has helped me track my daily intake/output as closely as possible for months now.  It can't help you lose weight or gain size or strength by itself, but it certainly can help you keep yourself on track. Highly recommended.

title: iOS 8.0 issues
body: Recently updated my iPhone to the new iOS 8.0 and this app isn't working right. I love fat secret calorie counter. Have been using it for over 2-1/2 years. I have tried deleting it and downloading it again on my phone but it seems to be hanging up on some of the screens. Please help fix it, I don't want to switch to another program.

title: Great app
body: Keeping tract of daily intake of sodium, fat, carbs and calories for health reasons has never been easier. Love this app!  Very easy to look up foods, find specific items or even add foods and recipes. This app includes brand name items and restaurant menu items. Can also tract exercise and weight. I highly recommend it!

title: Best food tracking ap!
body: As a health and fitness blogger, I'm asked frequently which is the best al for food tracking and it is BY FAR this one! Amazing database, so intuitive, easy and provides macronutrient analysis on the site and it has a great professional model if you're working 1:1 with clients. I have no idea how it is free, but I'm so glad it is!! I tell everybody!

title: Recommend to everyone!!
body: I have tried a lot of different weight loss apps and I have to say this one is the best by far. It is easy to use, easy to understand, and I love the fact that you have the entire Fat Secret community to cheer you on and support you. I highly recommend this app. It works!!

title: New to app but so far I am happy
body: Ok I have only been using one week but everything seems easy to navigate. I am sure I will continue to finds more tools to help me make good food choices with this app. After first week using this app with its RDI appearing very generous compared to WW. I have lost 2 lbs. I hope that I can continue eating healthy portions and make it a habit towards a healthier life.

title: Best out there!
body: I've tried several calorie counting apps and this one is far better than any of the others by far. It is easy to use, the barcode scanner is so convenient and the amount of food already in the system is amazing. Love this app and highly recommend it!

title: Simple
body: Very good app. Keeps track of your calorie, carb, fat, and protein intake. The barcode feature makes this a fast and easy way to keep track of the food you eat without having to take an hour to find it in a library of similar items.

title: LOVE this app!
body: I absolutely LOVE this app! I've had a hard time losing weight but from the first day I started using this app I saw improvement. It's easy to use and does all the calculating for you. It's so much easier sticking to this plan when you can see your improvement on your Weight History.

title: Excellent app
body: Great app for tracking your food intake and specially if you want to watch your micros. I love the fact that it brakes down everything. The only thing in think would be great when breaking things down, would be the "Sugars" or "Sodium" cuz when you train for specific goals would help a lot.

title: Tried several, this is the best
body: I can weigh in, I can plan my days meals, I can check my calories, carbs and fiber in and out for exercise calories and I can use it on the go and at the market.

title: Great but needs update
body: I like this tracking app much more than any other except I would LOVE to be able to change the meal names and number of meals like mymacros app. Being able to name them meal 1, meal 2 and so forth instead of breakfast, lunch etc and controlling the number of meals would make send and separating info out for my coach A LOT easier. PLEASE add this and update

title: Easy to use
body: A very helpful app. The food database is large and frequent used home made meals can easily be saved for future use. Exercise and a graphic display of daily basic nutrition are included, also. Over the past several years, I have found this to be very useful.

title: No ads like Lose It!
body: "Lose it" just added ads to their free version and I hate ads. If I could pay $10 to remove adds permanently I would've done that with no issues. I like how simple the layout is in this app and no ads on the free version! I would recommend to anyone.

title: Really impressed with improvements
body: I used this app about two years ago, and recently came back to it. The improvements are really impressive! I love the macro tabs and the easy barcode food add.

title: Great for tracking food intake
body: This is an excellent app!  You must be very honest with yourself and record everything you put in your mouth.  You are able to adjust your eating habits accordingly to achieve weight loss.  I would like the app to include daily water consumption to keep you on target too.  üëçüèΩ

title: Love this app!
body: This is a great app for weight loss and overall health. I can watch my carbs on each item along with calories. Plus, it has many items from frequented restaurants and even specific items to my grocery store. Also the exercise tracker is great. Very easy to get hooked on!

title: Who cares about point system
body: This app seems awesome. I really like the barcode scanner which also allows manual input. Plus it's free!

title: The barcode scanner does not work... But I love this app!
body: It does absolutely everything else flawlessly.  This app is awesome, and worth a small fee.  Only downside is that the barcode scanner won't work.  Nothing happens at all when I try to scan.  Manual input works fine, but I would live to save the time.

title: Has way more options than I even use it for
body: I mostly use it to monitor my weight changes and look up nutrition information of random foods. But their recipes are good too, and the app is quite nicely designed. I haven't even begun to use it to it's full potential.

title: Great for weight loss!
body: I lost 33 lbs in 4 months simply tracking every food I put into my body. I did ZERO exercise. I highly recommend exercise but I swear 80% of the battle is what you put in your body. I'm now back to lifting weights to gain muscle which will help maintain my body weight. Great app to keep you motivated and on track!

title: Love It
body: I've been using the website for years and the app for a few months. The app really helps with my busy lifestyle and automatically syncs to the website, which I so appreciate. I love the fact that I can track net carbs and other nutritional values that are important to me. Plus the food database is awesome!

title: Awesome App for diets or Diabetics
body: I have watched my intake since being diagnosed with Type 2 Diabetes. I used this app daily and it's just fantastic, counting calories and cut Carbs. Also it helps you track your weight and I will tell you it works! I recommend this app to all either medically dieting or just shedding a few pounds.

title: Great app
body: I love this app it has helped me slowly progress into a better change in my diet instead of being in a diet I'm making it a lifestyle and I'm loving how easy this app is making it for me! There still might be some updating that can be done with the food choices but over all I Love It!

title: Love it!
body: Best app for tracking calories, fat, sugar, cholesterol, etc. Easy to use. Easy to find most food available in stores and restaurants. Very adaptable to portions. Easy to add your own recipes, too. Loads of other recipes submitted by other users, too. Especially helpful with the Ketogenic method of weight loss!!!

title: Fit, (sorta) fast
body: This app has helped me a great deal with regard to my general fitness. It's easy to see set goals, and see your macros. But it's not perfect: I think it's a few too many clicks to get to your saved meals, and the app is flat out wrong about some of it's nutritional info(plain brown rice does not have 400mg of sodium!). But all in all, it gets the job done, and well.

title: A great app!  Very user friendly
body: I highly recommend this app to anyone who wants to lose or monitor their weight. It's simple and allows you to set and monitor your goals, watch percentages of food groups eaten and track essential nutrients.  You'll find any food item you're looking for.

title: Keeps locking up and closing
body: It worked beautifully for 2 weeks then it appeared the ads wouldn't load at the bottom, so it will freeze up and close out of the ap. I deleted and reinstalled, & it worked for another day, but then started freezing up again. Also, resets some parameters when i am entering "custom" exercise and food. Extremely useful when it did work.

title: Changes
body: The app will not let you change a meal from one day to the next and it was better when you could move things around through the meals and also not being able to see what you have for lunch to use it for breakfast or dinner makes it complicated also

title: Love it
body: Love how you can track everything. The way it displays it all. The only reason I gave it 4 stars because there is not enough tracking for the fitness. Like it doesn't even have logs for push ups. Other than that it's way better than the other apps. Love also you can make groups and challenges.

title: Amazing App
body: I am in love this app. I love how it takes all of my intake and breaks it down so I can see my macros. It's super easy to use and navigate. The only thing that kept me from giving 5 stars is that for some of the restaurant items you can't go in and take out things you excluded to show your true caloric intake.  Other than that this app is awesome.

title: Simple to use
body: I used the website before I had a smart phone years ago. There's just something about the simplicity of this app & website that kept me using it. I like how I can display the net carbs which is great for people counting carbs but get tired of subtracting fiber from the amount.

title: Ms.
body: I love this ap! It is very easy to use and rewarding as it allows you to weigh in whenever you want, tracks your foods and I love the graph that shows how you have portioned out your day.!

title: I love this app!!
body: It is so easy to journal your diet, keep track of your exercise, and your weight with this app. I've already lost 14 pounds with its help! I would say that you need to calculate your own calories based on what you want to lose. It seems like the app gives way too many.

title: Keeps me accountable
body: Having a daily budget of calories (calculated for me based on my physiology and my goals) is helping me plan meals better. Most of the foods I eat are in the database, which is nice, and if they're not, I can input my own data. So far, I'm on track with reaching my goal and seeing that keeps me motivated to continue making healthy choices.

title: Updates
body: I started this program a few months ago and quit. No reason other than off track. Started again this week and love the updates!  Much easier to use!  Gonna stick with it this time!

title: Weight Loss Buddy
body: I have appreciated the help and guidance Fat Secret has given me for years. Most foods are listed regardless of where you got them. If not you can add them easily. I also like the category lists such as favorites, most often eaten, recently eaten and search with four sub categories.

title: Greatest app for self control!
body: I love this app! ESP now that there is a barcode scanner.  This app makes me want to buy an iphone for my weight tortured mother.  And it's free!?!!!!?!?!!! Waaaaahhh? ;)

title: Pls fix these bugs!
body: App has numerous bugs but could be great. Bugs include no way to completely remove an exercise from a given day. Calculation errors (hrs calc) occur when updating an exercise activity. Needs ability to set # calories per day based on weight loss plan and then graphically monitor progress. Could be a great app but just not there yet! Pray that they read this and make updates soon!

title: Great app!!!!
body: Counts your calories perfectly. I lost weight instantly when I started using this app and working out consistently. It would be awesome if the "scan barcode" option would actually work, but typing in the barcode pulls up the item just the same! Great app!!!

title: How it helped me
body: As a male, 5'8", it helped me lose weight from 208lbs to 166. I feel fantasic. Its all about what you do for yourself and input it into this app. It doesnt do the work for you, except calculate your results. I would have given this 5 starts, except the newest version threw me off and I find it more confusing now. I liked what I was used to.

title: Cannot edit exercise
body: A pop up reads "Can not exercise" when I hit add on my iPhone 6. I'll give it 5 stars if this is fixed because this app is useless right now and I used to use it with my GS4

title: Best of the Bunch
body: I have tried a few calorie counting apps (myfitnesspal, Fitbit, etc.) and in my opinion this is the best of the bunch.

title: Great Tool -Fun
body: Found this app after reading reviews and trying several others. This one is easy to use, has a large food database. I am losing weight by tracking my food choice good and bad. Not 5 stars because 1 frequent no network 2 unable to edit journal notes on weigh in  and 3 lbs to go is zero. Little 'bugs, but app very useable.

title: Carol
body: Super easy to use.  I had another food tracker app and had to delete it because it was too difficult for me to use.  I use this app every day.  Can't beat the price (free, with no ads). I credit this app and my dietician with helping me be so successful in losing weight and becoming healthier.

title: Great app for tracking weight and macros
body: This UI for this app is much cleaner and easier to use than MyFitnessPal. The information seems to be much more accurate for foods. No ads or any annoying pop ups! Awesome app for tracking all your macros and weight. Highly recommended!

title: "The Secret"
body: This app has really helped me lose weight fast by monitoring my daily carb intake and other numbers. The holy grail of weight loss and getting in shape is 80/20. This app makes the 80 a breeze. You quickly start making better meal choices to keep your numbers in range. Thanks fat secret!!!

title: Love! More Restaurant Options!
body: I love this app. It has truly redefined how I look at food and weight loss. I am keep up with my log every day and I have seen amazing changes! I would like to see more restaurants represented. I like keeping track of even cheat meals and usually that is my frozen yogurt ;) Menchie's would be really great to add to the Chains list! Amazing app! I love it!

title: Almost perfect
body: This is the best weight and diet tracking app available. The only thing that could be better is having more foods available to add to daily intake. I do appreciate that I can add foods but this would not be possible if I were busier. This is still the most beneficial and comprehensive diet tracking app and I plan to keep with it!

title: Lost 13 lbs in a month
body: This is a very helpful app. I started using it to see why I was not losing weight. I faithfully entered diet and exercise. 30 days later I had lost13 pounds. Easy to use and many of the foods I eat are already in the library. Love it.  Way more intuitive than my fitness pal.

title: Glitchy
body: Won't let me restart from another weight after 'falling of the diet wagon' which was annoying. Support says "we can delete all your data so you can start over" ... Uh, yeah, no thanks. Want to keep my data, just want it to be right.

title: So easy to use
body: You can save meals that you eat more often, and a lot of things already come up with a barcode. It's been weeks and I haven't gotten tired of entering everything I consume yet because it's not a headache to do it. Love this. It's been extremely helpful.

title: Works great!
body: I exceeded my weight loss goal and lost 5.6 lbs in two months using Fat Secret. I'll continue to use for some additional weight loss and I really enjoy how much more mindful I am about what I eat. I find the app easy to use and I really like the calendar and calorie average features.

title: Very Useful
body: I just started counting my macros, I tried doing so on my note pad and just doing my best at calculating it. This app simplifies the process. Using this app I have lost 16pds and I'm still losing because I am able to keep track of everything I have taken in. Thank you!

title: LOVE FATSECRET APP!
body: This app has helped me lose 22 lbs. I use it faithfully daily. It is so nice to be able to plug in a food, and it is almost always already listed in the program. I also love the Recently Eaten Foods (list that I eat frequently). I now have the app loaded on my iPhone, iPad & laptop. It syncs everything between the 3.

title: My go-to
body: I've used FatSecret for years.  It's my go to when I want to track food and exercise.  I love the app and the website.  It integrates with my Health app on my iPhone, which is great.

title: Almost perfect diet log!
body: Great app! Really functions well with a nice and clean layout. The food is easy to look up and add, and the breakdown of different many different stats really helps to keep dieting on point. If only it could track more vitamins and minerals... (future update maybe??)

title: LOVE IT!!!!!
body: Was using Lose It and I was having to enter alot of the foods into the app.  Deleted that app when I found this one. This app has more in it's database than any other app I have looked at. You do have to have more than just calories when entering a new food but it is not hard to find.

title: Love it!!!!
body: Love this app! I can plan a whole day and know where I am for calories and makes me more accountable. Also by having my meals planned out, I avoid making poor choices! Love the barcode scan option and also the variety of recipes. Highly recommend it!

title: Best app for bulking/cutting
body: My workouts were always in place. Keeping in track of calories was hard until I came across this app. Definitely the best download. Has all the foods, from restaurants to create your own. A must have for goals with serious fitness!

title: Yes!
body: I really enjoy this app, the features are great. I think some notifications to remind me to enter my food would be helpful, I am terrible at remembering. Also, the app crashes sometimes which bothers me, but I really do like how the app works if it was smooth running every time.

title: Love this App
body: This app has a lot of the local restaurants which is very helpful. One thing that I would love to see soon is the ability to enter a custom calorie number for food that the app doesn't have. That way I can look it up somewhere else and enter it into the app so that I can still keep track of my day.

title: Easy to use! Lost over 20 lbs so far.
body: This app is very easy to navigate. I like the functionality of it. Inputting multiple food items is a breeze. Allows me to keep track of calories, exercise, and see with the monthly calendar how I'm doing. Thank you.

title: Better than fitness pal!!
body: Very accurate and thorough. Makes it easy to track your macros based on your specific diet needs and goals. Doesn't sync up with Apple Watch activity but can easily be logged in manually. Still a very enthusiastic five stars!

title: Amazingly Effective
body: Tracks foods and progress easily without needing to pay for upgrade. Easy to use and includes a database of many foods and brands you would normally eat. Anything else needed you can add yourself and it only takes a minute or two.

title: It has a macro counter!!
body: Love this app!! So easy to use, navigate, and adjust. I love that you can watch your macros bc I'm carb cycling. You can even adjust your daily levels of protein, fat, and carbs. I love the layout and it has a zillion foods. Not sure about international fruits and veggies, but its ever-expanding! Get it!! Use it! Love your body!

title: Really Helping
body: Keeping me disciplined and honest. Had a binge and after I saw how many calories I had just done it will help me stay strong next time. I wish it had a favorites section that I could store items I eat every day is all I would add. Highly recommended.

title: Love it
body: I love this app. I track everything including my water intake. I ignore the ads at the bottom, but it really shouldn't be political ads. My only problem is I can't change my goal weight. It will let you change it but won't store the change.

title: Great app
body: I've been using the website along with the mobile app for a while now. Having a quick and easy way to log my meals and my exercise has been invaluable in helping me reach my fitness goals. I would highly recommend it.

title: Best Weight Tracker Calorie Tracker
body: This is the best App that I have used to track my total health. It is visually pleasing, easy to use, has all the perks of all the apps out there wrapped neatly in one!

title: Great app but a little flawed
body: I love this app. It's real benefit is that it makes me aware of what I am eating. By inputting everything I eat, I have become knowledgable about which items are problem items (fried foods in particular).  My only issue is with the portions. Often, the only options are in grams or some weight - and I don't have access to a food scale while I'm out and about.

title: Love the community of this app
body: I have been using this site in general for 6 years and I love it. It is amazing to see how far they have come with their app! The community of people there are so kind and helpful. It is awesome to see my weight fluctuations and patterns between being pregnant and not.

title: Love this app
body: I was told to use this app to track protein and carbs. Didn't use it. Weight loss hit off yo slow start. Started using app and discovered high calorie intake. Tracking everything now. Weight is starting to come off. Really enjoy using it. Very easy to use.

title: Super Tracker!
body: Easy to use, easy to program and easy to gather information at a glance. The key features of this app is that you can program your macro intakes for the day, or judge your log by daily allotted calories. I would recommend this app over any other diet tracker!

title: Come a long way
body: The app has come a long way since its inception. It has a lot of new great features and a slick new design. I think the barcode scanning feature needs more work and the "most eaten" tab generates inaccurate data. I also would like to see the data for "recently eaten" go further in the past than, say, the last 10 things documented.

title: Easy and quick
body: It doesn't take much effort to log what you intake daily.. the hardest part is making sure the combination of foods fit your macros! The app is helpful for tracking weight and has almost all the foods I eat on a regular basis. Even when it doesn't, it's quick to enter in the necessary nutrients.

title: Wonderful and helpful app
body: The app isn't perfect by any means but it gets the job done for me.  One has to remember the purpose and intent of the app. I only wish I could monitor time of meals or have a self-set reminder. I don't want a separate app for that, but it's important for some to keep to a schedule.  I love that I can keep a photo log of my intake.

title: NOT USER FRIENDLY!
body: Too Complicated,  I was using "Lose It" but wanted to try another app with more features. For instance; How do I add to "Saved Meals"? I keep hitting "Save" everywhere I can, yet when I go to "Saved Meals",  it's not listed! How do I copy food from my Diary, I still can't figure that one out!  So dang frustrating! I wish I could see what the calories are based on what I've eaten before I save it. It's just not user friendly at all, thank goodness it was free! I give up, it's taken up too much of my time already... Too bad!!

title: Iphone6
body: New update works but it's more difficult to use. Under restaurants there's no more categories like dessert or steak or chicken etc. Under column it doesn't allow you to change rdi and calories. The old version was a lot easier to use because you could simply swipe left or right to go back a day or forward a day now you have to use some wheel to pick dates and the date on the wheel is off too...so much hope for this but was completely let down

title: Success !
body: First app that has  helped me lose since I've turned fifty. Easy to track calories weight and activity. Doesn't make you blow diet even if you've had your cheat. Just allow for it in your daily intake and you stay on track!

title: You Need Discipline
body: But to succeed with your goals that is what it takes. Cataloging your intake, exercise and weight will, if you are diligent, will certainly keep you aware of your progress. I can review past history record and confirm success or adjust for the future. Excellent app.

title: Fat Secret keeps me on track
body: Even a fitness professional needs a little guidance, and Fat Secret is just the right tool for me. Calories and energy expenditure are easy to track, and updates make the app more and more user friendly. I regularly recommend Fat Secrets to my clients.

title: Fat secret is awesome
body: This app is great for tracking food intake. If you are trying to lose weight or put on lean muscle mass this is a great tool for you. It is simple to use unlike other calorie counter apps, and puts u in control of your diet. The scanner for barcodes is great and saves time searching for foods.

title: Great App, detailed, great resources
body: I must maintain a food diary for health reasons. Love this program, there hasn't been a good item I couldn't find in the SEARCH. I really like this app and would highly recommend it to anyone who needs a convenient way to set goals and keep track of intake.

title: Not quite there yet
body: I really like this app a lot e.g. the awesome barcode scanner that also allows number entry. There's also a few things that could be better. First the fractions list for each item needs more increments like 1/8, 1/3, 2/3 etc. Also goals for individual macronutrients, remove items from search history or clear it. The recipe description should be optional.

title: Great Simple App With Few Flaws
body: I've been using this app for years and it has been the best calorie/fitness counter I have used.

title: Always a Good App
body: I have used this app on and off for a couple of years.  I have tried other apps as well and this is more intuitive.  I highly recommend it if you are looking to lose weight.  It really helps me to see where I am spending my calories and I can see when my ratios are off.

title: Notes on weight tracker has bug
body: I use the app primarily as a daily weight tracker. Nice to be able to see progress over time. However there is a bug in the note function. Notes tend to show up as duplicates for past entries in effect wiping out old entries. Makes the notes function pretty useless. Looking for a new app with a note function that works.

title: Great app
body: My husband I have both been using this app. He loves it for traveling and choosing meals in restaurants. I find the barcode reader and the food database very helpful. We both have lost weight using this app to track our food and will continue to use it.

title: Works Great for Me
body: I have been using the Fat Secret app on my iPhone since February and have lost 20 pounds in four months. I have discovered the recipe portion of the app and look forward to creating some great healthy meals. I told my doctor about Fat Secret and he recommended his staff check it out.

title: underrated calorie counter
body: clean, intelligent, and no BS counter. not a lot of bells and whistles because you don't need them. missing one star because it has a chain restaurant food feature that, honestly, I never use, but it might be useful to someone else who frequents restaurants where you can build your own order.

title: Love this app!
body: I have been using this app off and on for a few years and I love it!!  I can find almost every food item I eat and if I cannot find it, they made it really easy to add new items!!  Has really helped me monitor calories as well as fat carbs and protein!!

title: Really Good
body: This is an excellent app. Makes it very easy to track what I eat, and love that it is integrated with a desktop browser version.

title: Great App for me
body: We cook a lot at home, so I love that I can enter our recipes and track my daily nutrition.  It's also easy to add ingredients that aren't in the database.  It remembers what I ate lately, since I'm a creature of habit (when I find a recipe I like, I eat it frequently!) it makes journaling my meals a breeze!

title: Simple and effective
body: This is a great way to track macronutrients, caloric intake, and have a general idea of energy expenditure. The app is simple enough to use regularly throughout the day which is important for compliance. I would highly recommend it for any of my athletes or friends.

title: Love this App
