body: This makes being on a diet so much easier!  You know exactly what your putting in your mouth and I was surprised all the Restaurants that are listed!  Also the weight tracker is awesome!!  Like seeing the weight come off!   Thanks so much for helping me get healthy!!!

title: Fat Secret is a great way to track your eating habits...
body: FatSecret is an effective and easy to use tool to track your eating and weight. The interface is clean and easy to navigate. FatSecret shows you your caloric intake, macros, and tracks your weight using easy to understand charts and graphs. Try it, it's free.

title: Great app
body: Agree needs IOS8 update ASAP. Other than that this is a great app! Has tons more foods than other databases,  easy to use, has running totals at top of screen, (doing low carb so this is fab) doesn't throw in your face how much you have left to eat (which always bugged me) really happy with app. Will give 5 stars when updates for IOS

title: Fabulous
body: This is the easiest and most comprehensive food/calorie app I have used. It is surprising how many calories you eat unnecessarily if you don't keep track. This has helped me lose 45lbs so far, and I'm sure will help me with the last 4lbs I have left to lose. HIGHLY HIGHLY RECOMMEND!

title: Very professional, Awesome !
body: I've been enjoying the app and the website for years and it only gets better. It's free but it truly is worth money and I would gladly pay for this app. It serves a real purpose for me and I expect that it will continue to do so. Well done fat secret!

title: Mom and gymnastics coach
body: I have been using fat secret for over 3 months. I love it! It is so user friendly and I really believe that tracking what you eat is the big secret to weight loss and maintaining your weight. Tracking calories on your smart phone really works!

title: BEST App!  Love it!
body: I have had several apps, paid and free, to count my carbs and this app is, by far, the best and easiest to use.  Food and restaurant database is huge, and I love that it has a scanner. My only suggestions would be to add a carb limit (unless I'm just not finding where).  Awesome support too!

title: Very useful app
body: It's really help people to become more healthy and stronger. There are some issues with iOS and Web apps such as you cannot copy food from previous day on today. iOS app loose stops normally working when internet connection lost. But still this is great app and service

title: Diabetes help
body: Been using app for 2 weeks, has been great for my diabetes. My A1C has dropped from 7.6 to 6.7 in 14 days.  It gives you an immediate reading of number of carbs consumed for each meal which is vital in insulin injection. App is easy to use and works great with the Heart app on iPhone.

title: Really Helpful App
body: This app as been really helpful in tracking my food. It's has made me think twice about some of my food options. I find my self looking up some foods before I order so I will know about the calories and the sugar content.

title: It really helps A LOT
body: This app has seriously helped me a lot with my fitness journey. I highly highly recommend it. I'd say figure out your macros first though, then use the app to help on the log of your diet. The app was a bit off with my macros just based on my height and weight.

title: Awesome!
body: Way better than any paid app I've found. Far easier to put in a bunch of food at once to make a meal. When adding food, to scan barcodes, there's a camera icon at the bottom center. I didn't notice it initially. Fantastic app!

title: The Best
body: I had this on Droid and was looking for something similar on iPhone but luckily for me, the same app exists. It's just as good, if not better. Get some! Can be used for fitness tracking but super user friendly for looking up nutritional facts on just about anything!

title: Good program
body: I use WW and when comparing points with calorie intake I can see when some meals are too high in fat, etc. An addition of nutrient balance for ratios of carbs, fat, and protein would be beneficial to keep on track without having to use another program to calculate points. Other than that it's a good program.

title: Crashing
body: I used this on my droid, and my jailbroken 4s. Recently began crashing almost everytime I try to scan a barcode. Also, when trying to add food, some of the menu selections are too close together (such as search, recently eaten, and most eaten) making it very difficult to select that item.

title: The most simplistic, effective app
body: This app is excellent in not only keeping track of caloric intake and daily physical activity, but also very easy in keeping track of macronutrient intake (protein, carbs, fat), including the very important fiber.

title: Glitchy, does not work well
body: The app has a lot of good food data to select from but there are some problems with it. When I change the quantity of the food selected the app just closes itself. It times out a lot in the middle of searches and the barcode scanner doesn't work very well. Also, it has not been adding the calories up properly. When I open each food item the calories listed are correct but the total is incorrect.

title: Easiest way to track calories
body: Using this app makes it super easy to track all the calories coming in and going out... This has been the easiest way for me to lose the extra weight and maintain my goal weight. 5 stars...!!!!

title: Needs Water counter
body: Excellent calorie counter, but I wish I always had access to my saved meals, regardless of time passed or if saved as a breakfast, lunch or dinner meals. Too, and this is a big one, it needs a water counter. I must make sure I drink my 8 glasses of water a day, and this app. doesn't help me with that. Otherwise, really love it.

title: Fat (no) secret!
body: Got to love Fat Secret!  It is the easiest food journal I have ever used.  It keeps me accountable and for me removes the feeling of deprivation.  I eat every kind of food and keep portions in check.  When I reach my daily calorie limit I just stop eating!  Of course it requires a little common sense.

title: Excellent diet Tracker
body: Really enjoy this app as it has one of the best data bases and makes it's easy to search and the track food. Easy to use interface, my wish list would be an easier way to update your goals

title: Exacly what you are looking for.
body: Only changes I would need right now is a less detailed list of food consumed today. And I would ask for a larger font change where you put the weight or Count of this serving

title: Awesome App!
body: My mom and I both are using this app and we've both lost over 50 pounds combined.  This app will scan the barcode and will enter it into your daily journal.  That is awesome.  It also has popular restaurant nutrition guides and a weight tracker.  I absolutely recommend it.  There's nothing about this app that I don't like.

title: My favorite app!
body: I have been using fatsecret for over a year and can't live without it. It has been such a powerful tool in me reaching my fitness goals. Keeping track of what you consume as well as your daily activity forces you to make wiser choices. It's a very user friendly app and give it a thumbs up!

title: Solid & Innovative
body: I've had this app for a long time by different past names and on different devices. Always current and user friendly.

title: Great app
body: I love this app.  It's easy to use and you can create custom food entries for homemade meals. I love the display in the food entry portion showing protein, fat, carbs.  I don't use any of the social stuff right now just the food entry, weight tracker, and exercise pages!  Highly recommend this app

title: Quick & Simple
body: I have used other apps and this is still my favorite! It has a great variety of foods, simple portion sizes and it is easy to track favorite foods snd meals. It is also easy to log your exercise and weight. The price is right too.

title: Mrs
body: I have used this now for several years and it's great!  Can track exercise, dietary intake, etc and it gives you back quite a bit of data and trending ability.  The fatsecret community forums are wonderful and supportive; I've never seen anyone be dramatic or snippy.  I recommend this to my friends all the time.

title: Excellent
body: Great and useful! I used it on ad aily basis, all day and every day! It needs update from time to time, especially supplements, for instance, Iso Lea Pro by Labrada not available in App, which you can add by yourself , and what I like most about this app. All in all, it works fine I use daily!!

title: ‚ù§Ô∏è it!
body: I have never been a calorie counter but after 2 kids and almost 40, I needed to start. This app is great. Has lots of options, brands, already listed but adding homemade recipes or new items is easy too. Really liking it!!

title: Unhappy with recent update
body: Please remove photos of other users food that appear when the app is opened. I've used this app for years and love it however after the recent update, now photos of food posted by other users appear when the app is opened. As a struggling dieter, I have no desire to see pictures of other users food.

title: Love for years
body: I've been using this app for a few years now and they have only gotten better. Love the option to scan UPC codes and occasionally use recipes that always come out great!

title: Less then 24hrs in.
body: It has just turned off, twice, in the middle of entering a meal, and didn't save any of it. This morning it will only let me put in 4 items for breakfast, and in exercise it recorded a different activity, and I couldn't change it back.

title: Mrs
body: I absolutely love this app however it won't track my weight loss on my iphone 4s nor will it calculate calories used in exercise since it won't accept the weight I put in.  It also would be nice to be able to assemble a favorite recipe list.  Other than these issues a fantastic app.

title: Suggestions?
body: I love this app! It is easy to work with and I like how it is organized. I wish we could add a few things, for example: a spot for just water we drink during the day, a slot to make a list of medicine we take during the day, and a spot just for notes (how we felt that day, etc)

title: Best food list around
body: I have been using this app since July and it has so many foods already in it's database. With the exception of some crashes, I haven't had issues with it.

title: Bug with RDI function
body: It doesn't seem to take target weight into consideration. Plus, the current weight changes right after it is saved. (an automatic increase of .7 pound)

title: Thank you so much!!!
body: Currently this app is helping me track and of I eat and how much I eat, and helps me not to go above my calorie count. The results are magical and its exciting know the each time I open this app, I'm coming closer and closer to my goal. Definitely 5 stars.

title: Works well
body: I've used this app for 4 years now and it has some functionality that I really like. The ability to reset calorie budget when weight changes is a plus. It seems like some types of exercise aren't in the app anymore like various speeds of walking but I improvise.

title: Pretty straightforward and easy to use
body: I have enjoyed this application for tracking calories consumed daily and also for exercise. The database of food items is fairly extensive and rarely have to search elsewhere

title: Love it! Great app!
body: Has lots of great features from a huge list of restaurants and restaurant items to the ability to track your weight and exercise routine. No bugs and doesn't crash, no annoying ads, best app on the market!

title: Helped me track diet daily!
body: Easy to use and can't beat the price!  Helped me track my diet all the way down to nutrients.  The reports are great too.  Really kept me on track each and every day for the last 45 days.  Great app for those on strict diet.

title: Wish List
body: I wish you could select multiple items from a restaurant at once, instead of having to Save each item and start over.  Am I missing something?  Otherwise, I love it!

title: Love this app
body: 5 stars! The only thing I would like is to be able to pull different meals from different areas. Like take my breakfast and add all that to my dinner.. Sometimes you like breakfast for dinner. Or take one of my snacks and put that into lunch. Anyway, still love it!

title: It really works
body: I discovered the app on August 15 and weighed 255. It's now September 25th an this morning I weighed in at 226.6. The best part is I have had fun and have not been hungry at all. My goal is robe under 200 by if November and it this pace it seems that is going to happen!! What else do I need to say?

title: Great app, missing only 1 feature
body: I really love this app. It is so much better than other tracking apps. I only wish you could edit some meals.

title: Love this app
body: Use it all the time to track specific foods and calories. Like the ability to scroll and change amounts eaten & times for types of workouts. Keeps me disciplined to the end goal and already seeing results.

title: Love this app.
body: I have downloaded and tried quite a few apps. This one is perfect for me. It's clean design keeps things super simple to read and comprehend my macros.  I regained control from a weight loss stall and use it everyday now. Recommend it highly.

title: Pretty good
body: A recommendation: Can exercises be factored into the daily RDI? If I run and burn 600 calories, then really I have my RDI+600 calories to eat that day to maintain my weight/calorie goal. Otherwise RDI is a bit useless when you exercise a lot, unless you're happy to abandon the exact and work with averages. Or have to keep doing the math in your head.

title: Great!
body: I tried using MyFitnessPal to track my macros because I recently started a ketogenic diet. For some reason, it wasn't letting search the database for food. It was way more confusing to use than I remember. So I discovered Fat Secret, and I love it! It's easier to use in my opinion, and I can customize everything.

title: Perfect
body: Calorie counting doesn't work for everyone, but it's helped me so much. This app is free and perfect for keeping track of calorie intake and burn, as well as macro and micronutrients. It's taken me time to get used to just a different lifestyle, but have lost 10 pounds and counting with this app.

title: Makes it easy
body: Having so many foods in its database really makes it easy to enter calorie information. The barcode reader makes it so very simple when cooking at home. Almost addictive to use. Highly recommended.

title: Great app it should be the only one listed
body: This is the best app by far.  It does have a glitch where it closes for no reason.  Still it beats the other 8 I tried.  I even tried the nutrisystem app and a pay app.  This one is much better and free!

title: Same bugs still exist latest version
body: ***I keep reporting and they keep leaving the bug.*** Using another app pal.

title: Meh...
body: I like the app for what it is but there's nothing to set it apart. I am looking for a paid app with more advanced features.

title: The best by far!
body: This app is absolutely the best calorie counting app available. I have tried so many, but this one is the most comprehensive. It helped me reach my goal of losing 130 lbs in 11 months, now it's helping me to maintain a healthy weight. Thank you Fat Secret for helping save my life.

title: Great way to lost weight!
body: I've been using this app for years.  It helped me get to my goal weight and keep it off.  The ease of scanning barcodes, tracking exercise, and the integration with HealthKit is great.  It's definitely a must have app for those who are health conscious.

title: It's my favorite
body: I've went through many many apps trying to find help on counting carbs and this app is by far the best. It has every restaurant and food brand you can imagine... Makes type one diabetes a little more simpler.

title: Use it everyday
body: I use fatsecret everyday to track my macros. It does a great job with a ton of foods in the database and if a food isn't in it I can add it myself. This food log has helped me lose 20 lbs of fat, keep it off, and change my lifestyle to eating more healthy!

title: Saved all my info from 2009!
body: I fell off the food diary bandwagon about two years ago and went back to Fat Secret last week. And all my info and foods and exercise were still there! This has saved me a lot of time and typing. LOVE THIS APP

title: My go to app!!
body: I've been using this app for years.  Originally started using it to track my daily carbohydrate intake.  It turned into my diet conscious, if I didn't want to log it, I didn't eat it... I still use it to stay on track.

title: Easy to use!
body: Better than MFP (in my opinion) I'm actually able to calculate my macros freely. If I'm losing or gaining I can adjust the numbers on the fly without paying for a premium fee like my fitness pal. It's the small things that make a difference guys!

title: Very good app
body: There was a date problem however the latest update I downloaded 01/08, have solved the problem.

title: Love it!
body: I cook Puertorican food all the time and I love how you have calorie info for many of the dishes that I eat! I love how this app doesn't single out people who actually cook. (Other apps list only foods from restaurants or microwavable brands.) Great job guys!!! 10 stars hands down! =}

title: I don't like this app.
body: This sounds like a great app, but they are too controlling for my tastes.  Today I had chicken salad for lunch.  It's not in the database and I can't add it.  It seems that you have to submit foods to the group and have them approved.  This is not the kind of app I want.  So I'm deleting it.  Dictating what foods I can eat and can't eat and having to have someone's approval is ridiculous.

title: Fat secret calorie counter
body: Love this app.  It's been a key tool in my successful weight loss of 22 lbs.  if you're starting a weight loss plan, congrats!  Hang in there and know it takes time.  Do little things every day and lose it the right way, you'll feel great!

title: Best calorie tracker for free
body: I get a discount with weight watchers but this app is better and free. My main focus is keeping calories down. This pinpoints every detail of my day. Like the journal part to look back. Links to apple health app. Only thing is probably the name with the word fat.

title: Great app
body: I love this app.  Used it for a long time... Fell off the wagon with it a couple years ago but after finding all the weight I had once lost, began using it again.

title: Super easy and effective
body: I love how I can choose which micro or macro nutrients I want to focus on while not being overwhelmed with a lot of information. I've enjoyed using this app for the last month. Not going to use anything else.

title: Easy to use and keeps me honest!
body: I've tried a ton of other calorie trackers and I love this one the best! With the others, I felt like I was cheating myself with my calories and "burning" them, but this one has been keeping me honest. I love the grid because it's a good visual!

title: Awesome!!
body: This app blows my fitness pal. out of the water. I like how you can actually see the total macro count up at the top of each meal and don't have to go back and forth with the calculator. Deleted my fitness pal as soon as I started using this! üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª

title: Quality app
body: I switched to this app from MyFitnessPal.

title: Love this app!
body: This app has a better database then any other app. This app can be tailored to whatever kind of eating regimen you want. Only a few things would make this app 5 stars. Having a favorite foods, it does crash sometimes, and I'm unsure about a recipe builder.  Keep up the great work and thank you that it's FREE!

title: Nice!!!
body: Love this app...would be a 5 star app if it had a recipe folder. Hate having to search over and over for the recipes I find and want to make later. Would also be great if you could track your water intake. Fix these issues and this app would be top notch!!! Thanks.

title: Recipes
body: How about having a category for vegetarians! Even when I look at your "vegetable" category, many of the recipes call for meat. Thanks. Other than that, great app, but I would rather have NO space taken up for recipes than have these non-vegetarian friendly ones .

title: Convert from SBD app
body: A solid app (not repeatedly buggy). No constant requests to purchase a membership. The the fat/carb/prot percents and graph are very useful. The food database covers most of what I eat. Easy to add new foods. Have yet to work the recipe function. In sum: it works really well for managing effort to be healthier.

title: Great useful app
body: I love the way you can track your progress in all kinds of ways. You can check it on any of your devices and you can do and follow up on whatever diet or regimen you care to follow. Very practical and unobtrusive

title: Horrible
body: The Good:

title: Love this app
body: I really recommend this app to someone who wants to loose weight!!! This is very easy to use, has a lot of options asp if you like to control the portions, I found everything that I eat  a day, shows % of fat and carbs, love it!

title: Great
body: I really like the reports you can print from this app. The fact that you can also invite your dietitian, nutritionist or wellness coach to view your journal is very helpful when you are participating in a weight loss program.

title: Very easy
body: This app has made it very enjoyable to track my calories. It took one day to adjust to understanding how to enter everything then after that it has become rote. Thank you guys for making this app.

title: Works well for me!
body: This app works well for me, it's easy to customize, add exercise and it has a ton of restaurants. Plus if you're eating your macros it adds up every meal for you and gives you a percentage break down.

title: Wish I Could Still Use It
body: I used to love this app, until it started crashing all the time. Now you have to wait for the ads to load before you do anything, and they load so sloooooooow, I've finally given up. I don't use the app any more and am looking for a replacement. Too bad, because it has a lot of great features.

title: A well designed iPhone app
body: As an intermittent user of the website I can appreciate the thoughtful design of this app. It is much easier to use than the website making it childs play to track calories Nice job guys!!

title: Barcode Scanner Not Working
body: The scanner has only worked once for me, which is extremely frustrating... The saving grace is that if I can't scan, I can punch in the barcode -- w/out that option, I'd delete this in a heartbeat. I like the look of many other similar apps much more, but the other apps with scanners all seem to cost money to use in the same way I can use this app.

title: just one thing..
body: Love it! Only thing is i wish i was able to see the longer descriptions.. i.e. what it considers heavy or light calithenics... it cuts off the description and apparently doesn't share the iphones capability of going into landscape mode when u turn it... but otherwise pretty groovy.

title: Pretty good app
body: This app is very useful and can certainly help you achieve your weight goals ( no matter what they are).

title: Great App with P90X
body: I've been using this app while doing P90X and it has been a life saver. It takes all the guess work out of calorie counting, weight tracking and keeps your work in order so you know if you're eating enough.

title: Not easy to enter recipes
body: I'm having problems entering recipes via my iPhone 4. When I try to adjust quantities the app tries to recalculate all the necessary info, which then crashes the app. Honestly, things would be a lot easier if we can enter values via keypad. Otherwise, the app is great in helping me track my caloric intake & how much energy I burn.

title: Love this app but I want more
body: Hello I love this app I have been using it for 4 years however I really want a water tracker or water stars or a water tank build in the app! Overall love the app very easy to use and it's fun tracking everything it's really helpful!

title: Great app
body: I love this app! This food diary has helped me lose 40lbs and keep it off for a year.  It's very easy to use.  Unfortunately, the latest update has caused the app to "time out" several times a day for hours at a time. Please fix. I've never had a problem with this app before.

title: Great help to focus on better eating habits
body: I struggle with controlling my eating. Always surprised to see how poorly I choose the food I eat. This app helps my realize exactly what I eat and makes it much easier to control. And lose weight

title: Nutrition Pie Chart
body: I just started using fatsecret calorie counter. It has almost everything I need, except a nutrition pie chart. A pie chart allows the user to view the days nutritional values at a glance, i.e. carbohydrates, fat, fiber. It should also allow user to select which nutrients to view. Please consider adding this feature.

title: Awesome, recommended to everyone.
body: I really like this app. I like the fact that it keeps track of calories, carbs, protein, and fat. It works great and is easy to use. I also use the website which works great. The barcode scan was a great addition.

title: Love this app
body: I use this app multiple times a day and it is the best food tracker I've found.  Other apps want you to pay $5 just for the scanner alone and this one has it included for free.  The whole app is a fabulous tool!

title: üåüüåüüåü
body: A+ app this is a Super App  it really helps you keep track of every thing you eat and keep track. I wish it would have actual Excercise tapes though as energy burned. Like p90 x or 10 min trainer. That would be great and choosing intermediate, moderate or excelled

title: Love this!
body: I used to use this years ago on my blackberry and I just rediscovered it! Better than myfitnesspal and it does not minus the calories you burn on the graph so you still are aware of the calories you need to eat every day.

title: Very impressive
body: I absolutely love this app! The only thing missing is the heartbeat sensor option that I have to use another app for. Highly recommend this app to anyone who wants to keep track of calories consumed/expended with ease!

title: Opened my eyes to how much I eat!
body: Within one month (with moderate exercise) I lost 10 pounds of fat! It opens your eyes to how much you actually eat on a daily basis! The app has a search engine that is wide ranged with food options! It's a great app, love it!

title: Everything I was looking for
body: I use this to track my weight once a week. Originally I used it to track calories and everything was super simple to input and see.

title: It's Amazing
body: I love this app!! It does exactly what I want it to!!! Track my macros & it tells you how much eat food contains..If I could ask for anything it would be the choice to put your own macros in but then again this is good enough... ‚ù§Ô∏è love it!

title: Great app
body: I truly found a very helpful way to be more aware of what I eat, how I eat and what is full of carbs or calories - it's extensive library of foods makes it easy to pick from.

title: When it works, it's great!
body: I think this app is really great when it works. More often than not though, I get a message telling me the "network has timed out, try again later." Not handy! I think I'll keep trying a little bit longer because it really is a good app when it works, but I'm about to give up.

title: Awesome weight loss & fitness tracking program
body: This app is the best tool to help you track your food intake and fitness calorie burning. I lost over 30 pounds by honestly inputting my info. I have input every meal for past 5 years. Thanks!

title: Easy to use
body: I have found this app meets the many needs for accurate tracking of food intake, exercise and weight. It has a robust inventory of reference and nutritional tracking information.

title: Was perfect....
body: This app is intuitive and easy to use. It has 90% of the foods I eat need to track and was easy to see daily and per meal macronutrient breakdown.

title: Baby weight gone!
body: Using this app for the second time after having another beautiful baby girl! After gaining 50 lbs both times, I am back in my pre-pregnancy clothes at 4 months postpartum again! Love this app!

title: Better than MFP
body: Seriously this app has a ton of features that make it worthwhile. Tracking your food (including scanning barcodes) is very easy. Keeping track of exercise is even easier. And it's free!

title: Great app
body: This app has helped me lose 10 pounds over three weeks. It's good to be able to watch what I eat and know how much calories that I take in and out. I hope the developer keep adding more features.

title: Great for OMAD users!
body: I am doing intermittent fasting/OMAD, and was just curious as to how many calories I was eating at my one large meal. Pleasantly surprised at how many great features this has! I use it in tangent with the app "fasting secret," and the two compliment each other nicely. Thank you!

title: Easy, and user friendly
body: Easy to track what goes in your mouth. Track exercises and progress or regression. The BMR calculator is a little higher than others, I adjust accordingly. They stay on top of updates and improve the app regularly. I love it. Give it a shot

title: By far better than the rest
body: This site has been around far longer than i recall the others and I have been using it for years. I can do everything i need to - for free.

title: Fabulous
body: I love this application. It makes me totally accountable for what I'm eating. There aren't many items that aren't listed and adding one is a cinch. This is fabulous for those who are serious about exercising, counting calories and staying healthy and accountable.

title: Love the App
body: I love this app.  The scanner makes it so easy.  The sync feature is great.  Finally an easy way to log everything, making me accountable for what I eat.  I've lost 10 pounds the last month using this app.

title: Love this app! It's the best diet tracking app around!
body: This is the only diet tracking app I have used consistently because it has the restaurant menus and the barcode scanner! It's also very user friendly to navigate through!

title: Great app
body: I am constantly counseling patients on sodium and sugar intake. This app is quick easy simple to use. It gives information on not only total sodium intake but sodium per serving and tracks it. Unlike others that only look at carbs sugars and protein.

title: Love it!
body: This app has been the most reliable of all of the calorie counting apps and I've used it for years. I've lost over 100lbs and I honestly have to give some credit to fatsecret for helping me. Five stars and forever a loyal fan.

title: Awesome app
body: I love the barcode scanner but for some reason a ton of things that I could scan before all of a sudden aren't showing up anymore. It kinda annoys me but it's fine seeing as I can easily find a similar product in the data base or enter it on my own.

title: Updated for IOS8 - Now it's Super!
body: This app has just been updated for I OS8. It is working beautiful! Thanks a lot to the developer for getting this back online so quickly. It enables me to determine the proper insulin dose for blood sugar control.  You are a lifesaver.  Congratulations!

title: FatSecret
body: Pretty well organized. Good educational tool to understand where calories are really coming from and since I was on  a low carb diet it helped me to fine tune what I was eating. Overall easy to use with enough information present to keep accuracy high.

title: Love this app!
body: I have used this app for years! It is by far the best way to keep track of your macros and percentages. It has an extensive food database that makes it so easy to input your food, no matter what you are eating!

title: Great
body: It's easy to use.  It makes tracking your calories and macros super simple.  You can also track your exercise and weight.  It's a really nice looking and easy to use app that I highly recommend.

title: Now with export feature
body: Love the app! The new export option is awesome and works well. The app still crashes even after today's update. Today it was while using the barcode scanner. Hey I don't consider the crashing that big of a deal. Some OS's have been around a long time and still crash. Keep up the good work!

title: Weight Loss Surgery
body: Wonderful app. Having had WLS tracking protein is very important. This app is perfect for my needs. The barcode scanner works well. I deleted another app because the scanner never would work correctly.

title: Love this ap
body: I love this ap it helps keep me on track. Also love the recipes, easy to follow, taste great and are healthy, but wish there was a place to store my favorites. Sometimes find it hard to search for them again.

title: Great app; one small issue
body: I love this app.  Here lately though, whenever I hit the plus sign to add food to lunch, dinner, snack it always adds the food to my breakfast meal so I have to go back in and change it to the meal I want to record.  Using iPhone 4s.  Just curious if there's a fix for this.

title: New iOS 8 update ruined the app!
body: My phone did the new iOS 8 update yesterday, now my app will not work! Please fix this! I absolutely love this app but now that I can't delete anything after being entered it change amounts it is no use to me! I am now using another app!

title: Great app
body: This a great app, and easy to use. I like how it can sync with the health app, but I would like to see other features of the health app be able to sync with this app. Such as the step counter or distance walked or ran and have those stats be added to the exercise section.

title: Very functional
body: Easy to use.  Handy to have on my phone.  Sync's with my other devices.  Keeping track of calorie and carb intake, plus weight loss has helped me lose weight and keep it off.

title: Im surprised this app was free!!
body: Has a large database of foods, you can weigh in... This app keeps track of everything!!! The only thing I wish it did was a photo log (for progress tracking)... But thats ok, I have another app for that!

title: Works
body: Been using this app off and on for years. I used it to lose 80lbs the first time and now using it to stay in track. As long as you do the work this app will help you.

title: Excellent weight loss app!
body: This app is so helpful! It is easy to use and doesn't take a lot of time. I love that you can take a picture of a product, and FatSecret does the rest! I recommend this app to my friends!

title: Great - but one nuisance bug
body: Works great, lots of imbedded data, scanner works like a charm.  One bug ‚Äì  can‚Äôt create a ‚ÄúSaved Meal‚Äù  because the ‚ÄúSAVE‚Äù box is hidden behind the advertisement and can‚Äôt be move out to be selected.  Same problem with the RDI computation page  and Sync page and ??

title: This APP is awesome!!
body: I have used it for about 6 months now and I've lost 40 pounds and have finally hit my goal weight of 120!! It takes determination and really adding up every calorie but it seriously works try it!!!

title: GREAT app!
body: Love this app. Would be at goal weight by now if I'd have had it sooner. Love the new Recipe and Cookbook addition. Only complaint is it needs to add 1/3 and 2/3 measurements for items that have 3 servings, in which case the 1/4, 1/2, and 3/4 choices don't work. Otherwise SUPER app.

title: Best ever
body: I don't review for any app good or bad but this is an exception. I have been using fat secret for at least three years. Best app ever for tracking your calories and food. I used it on and off. It helps keep track of my weight.

title: Excellent tool
body: Very easy to use and helpful app.  Once you invest a little time in saving some of your favorite meals, inputting is a breeze.  I wish there were more exercise options, but that's a small gripe for a very useful app.  11 lbs and counting!

title: Great app!
body: I prefer this to My Fitness Pal because it makes your calories look less intimidating through the way they format everything. Super easy to use. I have no complaints.

title: Simple to use
body: Keeps track of daily food intake and exercise. includes information about common foods, even from restaurants. Tracks weight and goals. User friendly!

title: Use it religiously but...
body: This app is amazing. The database of products and food choices right down to Chipotle is fantastic. I use it daily to track my macros but the most frustrating piece is that the app on the iPhone constantly has errors/and won't let me upload my numbers. This happens daily. Please fix.

title: So easy to use & a great tool!
body: This app really helps when wanting to count calories, carbs and fat! It has really helped me watch what I eat and helps me with choices when I'm not sure if something is good for me or not!

title: I've lost weight.
body: It's as the title. I'm not obese or complex as other people that likely require a lot of effort, but this helped me track my calories easy. With limitation I've lost some weight. I'll keep going until satisfied.

title: Data connection required.
body: The app requires an Internet or cellular data connection to work.  While it may be possible to always have connectivity, FatSecret makes no bones about mining your personal data in the initial Terms of Service dialog that you must accept before using the product.

title: Recommended
body: Love using this app.   Being able to track weight watcher points is a definite plus and is what made me chose this app.  Would like more options in serving sizes but it is still the best out there.

title: Barcode Scanner
body: Live this app, had it on my droid before getting the iPhone 4. My only complaint now is that the barcode scanner does not work and this is a great feature. Please Fix......

title: Forgot password
body: Love this app over any other, just one problem, I've forgotten my login details and there is no place to recover this information. Please sort that out, or point me to a place i can do so

title: Great way to keep track
body: Easy to use. It's easy to personalize the settings to fit your own needs. As good as some of the apps that you have to pay for. Great community and recipes as well.

title: Easy to use, always in synch
body: FatSecret is a very straightforward, easy-to-use food tracker.  Pretty much anything you eat is listed.  It is easy to stay within the day's calorie range, and the at a glance setup makes it very handy.

title: Yes, it really is awesome!
body: I use this app daily. It's so easy to just scan your food into this app and have it track your calories and fat and weight that it's unbelievable. Awesome job, awesome app!

title: Fat Secret
body: Amazing and very helpful thing. It did help me finally start counting the calories and other stuff. Sometimes it works really slowly, but I think it's a problem of my phone not the app. Very satisfied!

title: Best help yet !
body: Love love love this app. Makes tracking your daily meals a breeze ! ( also love the help it provides when eating out w the restaurant menu info : helps me make better choices when out and about )

title: Great app.
body: Do the daily log shows you just how much habit eating and wrong foods you were eating. Seeing it total up every days makes you realize where you went wrong.

title: Great App!
body: Love this app! Love the barcode scanner. Was using another software on my laptop and I had to manually enter all the stats for every new food. This is so much easier! I'm already spoiled. Love the exercise and weight trackers too!

title: An Awful Update
body: The latest update is terrible!  When the quantity/amount of a food is changed, the nutritional information does not update immediately. This functionality worked well in the prior version. Also, the portion options are still too limited - especially the fractions scroll. Why do the programmers refuse to make this a stellar app?

title: Most useful app out there!
body: I never have trouble finding values for the meals I eat; the database is amazing! You can easily track your weigh-ins, progress, calories burned etc.. Great recipes and meal suggestions for any diet you are on. Congrats on a great tool!

title: New update broke what didn't need to be fixed
body: The new update pretty much broke the exercise tracking. Nothing seems to be improved in new version, but less data is presented on screen. I'm sure I'll get used to new formatting, but it's disappointing that the exercise tracking was broken.

title: Love it. Just needs step counting for calorie adjustment
body: This app is clean, simple, and works well. I hope the developer(s) add step counting data from the Health app and have it factor in to calorie intake.

title: Love!
body: I love this app! I've tried other diet tracking apps and I always compare it to FatSecret. The updates on the app are ALWAYS helpful and never pointless. I been using this app for years! I will never delete this app.

title: Great Calorie Counter
body: Excellent food search menu with every type of food you can imagine.

title: Nice app
body: Easy to use and definitely helps you monitor caloric intake. I've tried all kinds of approaches for leaning out, and at the end of the day it's all about diet. This app makes it easy to track any food or drink which helps significantly with fitness and weight loss. Great app!

title: Love it!
body: I found this a few years ago and it has really helped me keep my weight on track. It is very intuitive and lets you set up repeat meals for quick entry.

title: Great app
body: Great app easy to use and works fine for keeping track of your weight and diet every food that you can image is easy to be found I don't want to be a fat person Thanks

title: Crash!
body: This was the most practical app on my phone until thevlatest update. Now all it does is crash and always at random times. I think it's the new ad banner, which I loathe. I would gladly pay any amount for a version without this distracting and in the way banner. Please offer a version without ads!  Fix the crashing and remove the ads and I'll give it the 5 stars it should receive.

title: Fat Secret app is changing my life!
body: I am changing my eating habits because of this app. I am now concious of what I eat because I understand what my calorie intake should be. The best 10 seconds I have ever spent was when I downloaded this FREE app! Thank you, Fat Secret!

title: Used to work
body: I used this app a couple of years ago and it was great. The latest version though drives me crazy. I constantly get network time out error when I try to enter food. It can take 5 minutes of trying over and over just to get a food entered. Please fix!

title: Really like this app
body: This is my favorite calorie counting app by far. I do wish there was a multi-add function. I hate having to go through all the search steps to add multiple foods at the same restaurant. That's the only think I would change.

title: Does the job
body: This app actually works. No crashes, no complicated instructions. It just works. One caveat: some of the food entries are inaccurate regarding calories. Probably manually entered by other users.

title: Useful and intuitive

I'm supposed to be turning in 2 months worth of food journals. Guess I will not be doing that. :( really hoping this is something that can be fixed.

My boyfriend told me today he just realized his was not counting correct calories for fats! Fix these issues or I will be deleting this app very quickly!  He has already made the switch.

title: Been using it for years

I deleted the rest and used this.   Over the years I have been testing out newer calorie counter apps that come out just to see what they offer but nothing compares to Fat Secret. title: Long time user first time reviewer üòä
body: I have been using FatSecret on and off for over 10 years. I originally used their website and transitioned with the app with various apple and android devices.

title: It Helps Me Accomplish What I Couldn‚Äôt Do On My Own
body: I use this app in conjunction with the website to track calories and activity. It's useful and the large food database and ability to add foods to it are very much appreciated. It needs a way to sync data between the app and website and from one day to the next on the app without having to close the app and reopen it. That would make me change this to a 5 star review. UPDATE 11/9/2020: They have tweaked the app. It‚Äôs more user friendly and the layout is easier to work with. And it syncs now! Still the absolute best food database IMO. They have made it easy to update nutritional information. I used to have to use the website periodically to do certain things the app couldn‚Äôt do, but now I am able to use the app 99% of the time. It never crashes or acts weird. I‚Äôm able to easily track micronutrients as well as macros, which is invaluable in keeping my sodium intake, and therefore my blood pressure, in check. And it works! You must be diligent and weigh/measure when necessary and be honest! The app literally shows you what works and what doesn‚Äôt. I am 61 and quarantine wasn‚Äôt kind to me weight wise. With this app I have lost 14 pounds since June! Be diligent, be honest, and with this wonderful app, anyone can lose weight.

title: Really great app
body: I‚Äôve had this app for a while. Did not use it for the entirety of 2018 (personal issues üòî), but came back to it. All of my info still here as if I had never gone off it.  I love how easy it is to use. Had it initially on Android, switched to Apple.  Easy to use on both platforms.  It‚Äôs actually fun using it as a food diary to record my meals, it is helpful to planning meals ahead of time because i can look at previous meals for nutritional info and see how they can fit into my meal plan. The users are all encouraging of others, a BIG plus.  Enjoy seeing what other peoples meals look like, get ideas and inspiration from them. The best part of this app is that you don‚Äôt feel like its an isolated, static app, you feel ENGAGED in a live, vibrant community where everyone‚Äôs goal is to be a healthier, better person and want the same for each and every person.  You can track your fitness/exercise as well as meals and monitoring of weight. It can calculate your individual recommended caloric intake based on your input values so you can adjust what you eat based on your goals of losing, gaining, maintaining. And its super easy to use.

title: Update ruined app!!
body: I loved this app until the update yesterday! First it wouldnt open at all, so I had to delete & reinstall it & lost weeks of food diary entries in the process. 2nd after I reinstalled it, it would close out after every entry I made (slightly annoying when you are trying to log for an entire meal or DAY!) 3rd and last straw: now the app will not even work AT ALL! says "network has timed out" & crashes everytime I try to do anything!! I loved this app. It was my fav calorie-counter out there. I used it everyday religiously as I am trying to gain weight. But now that it's crapped out I'm using My Fitness Pal or whatever and I was impressed & pleased to see that this app actually gives you the option between whether your goal is too lose OR GAIN weight! NONE of the other apps offer that...I always had to lie about my height & weight or it would tell me I'm underweight and should not be dieting & to consult a physician! LOL.  I'm happy with "my fitness pal" it functions properly & has everything that the FatSecret App did, also is free -so I recommend it to anyone who used this crashed app!

body: Love this app! Effectively helps me monitor what goes in my mouth. Great for low carb, WW, etc. Bar code scanner is such a time saver and probably my favorite feature. Can add recipes, then get nutrition info. Can add single food items. Even has some restaurants. Endless ways to monitor.

title: Camera Update...no good
body: Since adding the option to take a picture, the barcode scan barely works.  If I use the camera option, then I am still having to search for the item if there is no exact match.  Might as well just search rather taking the extra steps to take a picture. It's annoying to enter the bar code numbers when it worked so well before.  Please fix the scanner, otherwise, I'm out.

title: Love this app
body: Very user friendly I can find almost any food by brand or even restaurant choices. Really like the bar code option.

title: Garbage compared to the alternatives
body: There's a lot to hate in this app and very little to love.

title: Good, almost great
body: First off this is a very pretty and useful app. Looks great, simple at first glance but has a lot of detail if you need it. Little bit of extra tapping to add foods compared to others but not horrible.

title: Love it
body: Great app,free and not full of ads.love it.10+

title: Best calorie tracker
body: I believe fat secret is the best calorie tracker hands down! I've used MyFitnessPal & Lose it before. Fat secret is top for 1 reason. U can input all foods in grams and that's so convenient. Btw, check me out on YouTube; Mr. Go-in  I post fitness videos, tutorials, & nutritional meals.

title: Great app!
body: This app helps me to be healthy and accountable. I've used it for a couple years and tells me a lot about what I eat. My only complaint is it is now missing the bar code scanner.

title: Easy
body: Easy to use.  Lots of food options to track.  Straightforward to set personal goals even at macro level.  Many reports both visual.and derailed numbers.  Overall excellent app.

title: Best tracking macros app bar none
body: I've tried the top two apps in the market and this particular app is not only thorough, there are no charges for upgrade of services, unlike the other apps out there. Great experience in terms of ease of use, extensive food database, bar code or search option, tracks macros by list and graphs tracks goals in weight, nutrients, calories burned, etc etc, everything the other apps do plus this one has a daily notes feature and I can customize any feature  ....all for free. Love it!!!

title: Awesome
body: My friend has been doing weight watchers and I was looking for an app to help me. This has been perfect and it is free. I have been able to track everything very simply.  I love the bar code feature. It makes shopping and tracking so easy. I like the way it keeps track of recently eaten items or exercises. We are creatures of habit and usually do or eat something a couple days in a row. I usually load my usual items in first thing in the morning. If I pack my lunch I load that info as well. Then when I get home if I haven't eaten something I can subtract it. I have shared the app with at least a dozen people who really like it.

title: Excellent
body: Excellent food logging app through bar code, it's own database, and adding foods manually to the database.

title: Very good App
body: Easy to use, organized.

title: Saved my life!
body: What an awesome App! I was classified  as obese when applying for life insurance & 5' 7" tall I weighed 245 lbs and at risk of diabetes & heart disease. I found this app & plugged in my goal weight as per my insurance company's guidelines and with that I was told the number of calories I should be eating daily! I was surprised to see what a "serving" is compared to what I was actually eating! Using the app & some exercise...yes you have to exercise....I am now 188 as of today 1.10.16 no longer obese, insured at a normal rate, no longer in danger of diabetes or heart disease. I plug in what I eat which means I DO NOT DENY myself of any foods & I exercise. Please note it takes time....it took me 3 years to drop the 50 lbs but I've kept it off for 3 years!!! Good Luck!

title: Easy to use
body: I love the new bar code scanning feature and the fact that it has so many brands and restaurants available to search from.

title: Excellent!
body: I've been using this app for a month and have lost 9lbs. Really like the bar code scanner and the vast library of foods and restaurants!

title: Amy
body: I love this app because it keeps me accountable and there just aren't anymore excuses for not charting what I eat. I know for a fact that I don't need 2300 calories in a day... I'm on a weight loss program. I just chart what I eat and my exercise. It's really that simple. If I can't find my item, or the bar code reader can't read my barcode, I can put put my item in. I Love it!

title: Pretty good but still needs work
body: The food database is very good and the search engine is excellent. It allows to add new foods, which is a great feature. Also, for almost each food one can enter a custom portion weight or size. Packaged foods can be easily entered by scanning the bar code. Negatives: it does not track potassium or vitamins. It does not allow to enter a custom food recipe.

title: The Best App Ever!!!
body: I think I have tried most Apps on weight loss. Fat Secret in my  opinion is the best. Love the bar code.

title: Great App
body: This app is easy to use and has great tools.  The bar code reader works consistently and has never  "not found" an item.  I especially like the option to add a new food I make at home and have it available for future use.

title: Nice
body: Nice app.But please work on Ukrainian version.Thank you.

title: I really like it
body: Have used it for some time and think it is the best one. But now with the upgrade I can't get the bar code to work. It asked me once to access my camera had never asked that before and I said no and now the bar code feature does not work. Any suggestions.

title: STILL no sync w/HealthKit
body: This is the best app for what it does, but what in the world is taking so long for syncing with HealthKit?!?  Also, the dates are still screwed up, even after the 10/7/14 update. It's always a day behind.

title: With last update Bar Code Scanner no longer works
body: This is by far the best calorie counting app I have ever used allows you to log all aspects of fitness. However with this recent update in the last week or so I have lost use of the barcode scanner which is a real bummer since that was one of the best parts of this app. Please fix

title: Great!
body: Easy to use. Great data base. Can adjust to your own RDI and diet. You can adjust list to count fiber or protein or carbs etc.

title: 4-13-15 Update Awful
body: The current update added as of April 13 2015 has rendered this app useless. It crashes and or times out in both the iPhone and iPad version. Come on guys. Simply Ridiculous!

title: Can't search any Indonesian food from this app
body: After i downloaded the app, I can't even search any of Indonesian food from the app. But it's exist on the fatsecret.id.

title: I love this app!
body: I love that this app is user-friendly. The feature where you only have to scan a barcode and it and 99.9% of the time always has the nutritional information stored is wonderful.if an item isn't already in the database, it's extremely easy to add an item. I really like the feature where it tracks your daily or weekly progress. And it calculates your calories for your needs whether you want to lose weight quickly slowly maintain your way eight and then it tells you how many calories you can eat per day.

title: Excellent and Easy to make a daily habit
body: The food entry is really simple and the bar code reader really makes the phone app terrific.  The only piece of info I'd like is the net calories between food intake and exercise,which you get on the website.

title: Fantastic!
body: Amazing functionality. It actually makes counting calories (and mgs if sodium) easy and fun. Without being able to look up nutrition info based on restaurant names, brands, or bar code (which the app makes easy), I'm sure I'd never bother. The weight tracker is also great. (I wish I could view the weight graph and a calorie graph simultaneously.)

title: HATE the iPhone version!
body: Ok, I don't ever write reviews. In fact, this is my first. Let me start with a small disclaimer...I'm a tiiiiiny bit OCD, and probably more fanatical than most in journaling my daily exercise and caloric intake. With that said, I am so unbelievably disappointed with this app. I previously had a Droid, and I LOVED Calorie Counter...used it all day, everyday. At my biannual upgrade, I (against my better judgement) switched to the iPhone 4S, and the features and functionality of this app completely changed!

title: Like it
body: I downloaded this app for my iphone because I needed to track my protein intake. However, it tracks that as well as fat, carbohydrates, and overall calories which I have come to find useful as well. I have not had a problem with the bar code scanner. I've successfully scanned several items from Trader Joe's. I like the feature that helps you calculate how many calories per day to set as a goal to achieve your desired weight.

title: Bar code reader, decimals
body: I just started using the bar code reader and I love it! No, it doesn't read everything but it saves a lot of time when it does. Just make sure you hold your phone steady when using it.

title: When it works it's great
body: I have been using Fatsecret both on the web and via this app for eight months. The app is very handy, especially for bar coding information from new foods. Unfortunately the bar code function has a tendency to lock up. Usually when this happens it will clear itself within a matter of minutes. Recently, however, it locked up and blocked me from using any functions in the app. It would not clear out even after more than 12 hours. I finally had to delete the app and then re-install it.

title: Bar code reader needs improvement.
body: Good app. Bar code reader is slow and shaky - need to use keyboard entry often.

title: Glitchy
body: The scanner does not read; when I tried inputting the bar code, the screen then asks to type in the food but the numerical keypad stays there.

title: Scanner
body: I love the app. It is easy to use and pretty quick to navigate. The search function is decent. My only complaint is the bar code scanner. It rarely scans anything. I end up punching in the bar code numbers.

title: Use to be a lot better
body: I use to use this app religiously back when it was called calorie counter and it helped me lose a lot of weight. I just redone loaded it, and I must say it has taken a turn for the worst. I love that you can find a more precise calorie count with the weight conversions available, but the GUI is less user friendly then it use to be. I also can't get the dam bar code scanner to scan anything any more.

title: Great app but
body: Great app but i think there should be an option to add the macros manually if there is no bar code to scan. The % of macros would be nice too... But not necessary... Other than that its a great app... I use everyday and love it...

title: Good data base, but crappy bar code scanner
body: This app would be awesome if it had a better bar code scanner. I've used other calorie tracking apps that the scanner doesn't even have to focus the get the code. This one on the other hand is very finicky. You have to hold the scanner just perfectly to get it to work. Other than that, it's great. Very user friendly and has great restaurant information. If they fix the scanner, this app would be without equal

title: pretty good but could be better
body: Edit:  since the last update, the bar code scanner works great!  Thanks for the fix.  I am back to loving it!  End of Edit.  In general, a very good app.  I have lost 25 lbs using it.  I do have a few gripes:

title: So far it's an excellent app!
body: Edit: I am using this on my iPhone 4 and see that it crashes now and then  but that isn't interfering with my using it everyday.  I still love this app. End Edit.  It is visually appealing and will no doubt help me watch what I eat. And the bar code reader is awesome. I would definitely recommend. It has everything you need!  Thank you for such a fine app!

title: A lot of freezing and resets and the bar code scan doesn't work
body: I have been using this app off and on for awhile now and I think it has a lot of great features and is easy to use, when it doesn't reset, and the developers have made a lot of great improvements. However, they need to do a better job of quality testing before release.  The bar code scanner is not working correctly for the itouch and you can't enter a bar code manually without going to the scanner function first, which would be fine except the application will not respond until I go out of the application and re-enter.  Then, 85% of the time the app will reset.  That being said, I like the features they are including, especially when they get the bugs worked out.  I would like to ad my agreement with another user, it would be nice to be able to add a dish, set the serving size, and then be able to recall that dish specifying the serving size, or portion consumed at that time.  One last suggestion, many of the dishes will not allow you to designate a small enough fractional portion.  Example; if I have 1 and 1/3 cup serving, 1/3 is not available so I have to use 1/2 or 1/4, if a serving is 350 calories, that is a difference of 28 or so calories.  Decimal size portion of a 1 serving size works great, then you can enter a decimal fraction of one serving.

title: Pretty Good
body: I have an iPhone 4S. I have not had any issues using the barcode scanner, so far. I usually hold it so that the red line covers the entire bar code, after a couple of seconds of holding it still, it will focus and accept the bar code. I was also able to enter a new item's info easily after the item's bar code was not found in the system. (New diet soda variation.)

title: Great app for free
body: This is a really nice app considering it is all free and I have yet to see an ad. It is easy to add food and exercise on the go and synchs with the website. I also like that it breaks down your food by what meal you ate it for, it helps me realize if i skip meals.It could be a bit more comprehensive in the review of the food you eat, but it is free so I'm not complaining.

title: Really great!
body: Bar code issue and ceasing issue MUCH better since recent update! Already lost 16.5 lbs using this app! The key is to save meals so you can add them easily. Also it helps me to plan what I'm gonna eat the day before so I don't impulse eat.

title: Please fix the scanner
body: I love this app except the barcode scanner freezes and you can't type in te bar code number.

title: Excellent
body: Excellent app but need to fix the bar code feature! Doesn't work

title: Useless for cooks
body: If you cook anything more complicated than a boiled egg, this is not the app for you. There is no way to create a recipe and then divide it into portions. You can create a meal, but each element of the meal gets listed in your diary, and the total can't be portioned. The bar code scanner isn't great, either. This app needs a lot more work.

title: Updates Please!
body: I like this app. As u can tell by my rating. The only constructive criticism I have as of now is that it would be nice I have an easier "delete" option for the food diary. I was thinking of integrating the apple way of sliding across an entry and having the "delete" button come up.

title: Works good so far
body: This program has alot of features.

title: Good one
body: This app is really helpful. Though I feel calorie per day is listed more than other apps... Love the huge food db...the camera capture is not working, but still can use code

title: Bar Code Scanner
body: I am a very happy person today.  The bar code scanner now works on my iPhone 4!!!

title: Good, except for the scanning barcode.
body: I had this app installed on my Droid and it worked great.

title: Great app and it's FREE!!
body: I really like this app and it's super easy to use. I would make it a 5 if there was a place to track water, enter your own food (if the bar code didn't recognize something, etc) and if the saved foods didn't save which meal it went to. But overall, amazing!!

title: Gray app with a few glitches
body: Great app with a few issues. I used to be able to change my RDI to whatever I wanted and now it's pre-calculated. The bar code scanner is a great tool but 1/2 the time I go to use it, the app closes (a little frustrating). Otherwise I have had this app on both my I-phone and my droid and it has been a great tool for tracking my nutrition and excersize.

title: Great app!
body: It does occasionally crash, but loads fast. Bar code key pad is hard to load. Overall very useful and easy to use and understand. The restaurant/ fast food info is wonderful if you eat out a lot and want to be healthier.

title: Shrinking by the minute!!
body: I LUV LUV LUV this app!! Can't believe it's FREE!! It helps me stay accountable for everything I eat! My only two complaints is that for one it calculates everything under the sun but DOES NOT allow you the option to track points : (. I follow Weight Watchers so that small glitch is critical. Also the bar code scanner is VERY slow and generally cuts off / crashes before logging the UPC code . Other than that this app is fantastic! It has nearly every restaurant imaginable NOT just fast food chains PLUS it has every food you can think of on the market and even shows you a photo just incase you are fearful you may be logging the wrong foodÓê†ÓÄéÓÄé TWO THUMBS WAYYYY UP!!!

title: Excellent! So easy!
body: I usually abhor keeping track of my calories, but this App, and the online version (they stay synchronized!!!) ate fantastic. The database seems pretty huge and if a food is not in it, you can add your own by scanning the bar code (sooooo easy) or by entering the data manually. I love it.

title: Great app
body: I've tried a few others and this one has more accurate nutritional values. When you. scan a UPC code it should be correct. Other paid programs have been wrong

title: Somthings missing...
body: Where is the option to take a pic of the bar code?  A friend has it on their verizon droid.
Great app!  Will get 5 stars once they add the bar code scanner

title: thank-you!
body: the bar code scanner is great!  Makes the whole process of entering food into the diary quick and painless.

title: One of the best
body: I've been looking at all of the descriptions and features of similar apps (Free and with a cost), and this one has by far the most features.  It is also easy to use and you can even "SCAN" the bar code of an item to upload the nutrition information for that item.  It is a great app.  You need however to have a little patience when using it because occasionally you get a message stating "network not available" and you have to try your operation again.  Calories burned per activity seem pretty accurate according to your weight, height and daily activity level.  I would recommend this app...PLUS it is free, so you have nothing to loose :)

title: Big mistake
body: Was the best, I told anyone who would listen about it... Updates ruined it. No more points, WTF? Won't be on my list for long. I will have to find something else. Very disappointing

title: Got Lucky with WW update
body: As everyone has said, in recent posts, this app is no longer a 5-star app since the update. I got lucky and updated via the iphone and noticed the weight watchers points were gone. so i deleted it from the phone and hooked up to itunes, where the older version was then put back on my iphone. now I will always have that red circled "1" next to my apps icon but it is more than worth it!

title: barcode scanner still not working on the iPhone4
body: Verified that the latest update fixed the issues on a iPhone 3GS, but my iPhone4 (4.0.1 IOS) still doesn't work with bar code scanning. Tried all kinds of barcodes, at various angles, in various lighting conditions, with no success. Hoping it's just a quirk with the iPhone4 hardware.

title: love the bar code feature great addition
body: Great app and website!!!!

title: Fat secret
body: Fat secret has been very helpful to me for loosing weight

title: Not bad
body: It would be nice if you guys would add some vegetarian recipes

title: Only decent app for tracking macros
body: None of the other calorie trackers make it as easy to track grams of fat, carbs, and protein as this one.
